title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Stir in the cream cheese until melted. Add the chicken soup and top with onion rings.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low.
Can also be put in pan and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: patio tuna squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2 inch up sides.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over dough; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until edges are light brown, about 30 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 items together, then pour in the 16 ounce can of drained blueberries.
Pour into Bundt pan and cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries, stir in sugar and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Mix Jell-O into hot water and let cool.
Then mix remaining ingredients with cranberries.
Add to partially set Jell-O.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon together in one bowl. Then put water, margarine, oil and cocoa in a double boiler and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Then mix buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; add to batter.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Then spread chocolate icing on it.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Then mix dry ingredients with first mixture.
Do not beat too long.
Last add hot water and mix well.
Put into small 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° in muffin tins. Mixed batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mexican rice and beans
directions: Mix beans, 1 1/2 bean cans water, 1/2 packet ham flavor, 1 packet sazon, lots of adobo spice, tomato sauce, sliced potatoes and flour.
Cook over medium to low heat until potatoes are tender.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, salt, water and sugar in a bowl; add flour.
Put dough on wax paper and knead.
Cut off pieces and make into pretzel shapes, not too thick or thin.
Put on cookie sheet. Brush with beaten egg.
Make sure to cover all surface of pretzel with the egg.
Then sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, until browned.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift into bowl with the salt. Add the shortening and use a pastry blender or two knives to cut it into the flour until coarse crumbs are formed like peas.
In a small bowl combine the beaten egg with the vinegar and water; drizzle over the flour until it is all moistened and holds together in a ball.
Add a little more water (a few drops) if needed.

title: veal paprika
directions: Dip cubed veal in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Brown in skillet.
Drain skillet.
Add the gravy and 2 cups milk with 2 tablespoons vinegar for each cup milk.
Cover skillet and let simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over wide noodles.
Serve with side dish of cole slaw.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add pumpkin.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Add water.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: patsy's trash
directions: Mix dry ingredients first in a large bowl.
Mix all liquid ingredients in small bowl and pour over dry ingredients, mixing well until all ingredients are coated.
Put on cookie sheets and bake for 1 hour 225°.
Mix every 15 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Fresh milk with 1 teaspoon of vinegar may be substituted for sour milk.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in a two-quart casserole dish.
Mix cheese, sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle with margarine.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over butter, then spread peaches on top of mixture.
Using juice from the peaches or milk to make up 2 cups of liquid; pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: forever amber candy
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 10 x 5-inch pan for 30 minutes at 275°.
Take from oven and spoon into bowl of powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
It's delicious.

title: cheddar squares
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain and press out water. Combine flour and baking powder; add eggs. Mix, then add melted butter and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. When cool, cut into squares. Serve warm or cold.

title: coffee cake braid
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine milk, shortening, sugar, and salt.
Cool until lukewarm. Add eggs and then yeast mixture.
Stir to blend.
GRADUALLY, add flour that has been sifted with the cinnamon.
Add fruit.
Mix to form a soft dough.
Knead lightly, on a floured surface, until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until size doubles (approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Divide dough into two equal parts.
Cover and let rest for ten minutes.
Roll each part into a rectangle, 1/2 inch thick.
Cut each rectangle into three lengthwise strips.
Braid the three strips into a loaf form, sealing the ends.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until size doubles (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While warm, glaze with confectioner's sugar that has been moistened with a few drops of water and the vanilla.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix, 1 egg and shortening in bowl; mix until crumbly, then measure 1 cup and set aside.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Beat remaining 2 eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice until light and foamy; pour over hot crust.
Sprinkle with reserved 1 cup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix well.
Cook 15 minutes and can.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add chopped chillies and other remaining ingredients except cheese.
Line bottom of dish with Tostitos.
Pour hamburger mixture over Tostitos and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: helpful hints
directions: Combine and after mixing well, store in spice shaker with a tight lid.
Keep in cool dry place.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Crush shrimp and mix with other ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli finely.
Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble it.

title: peanut pie
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer for 15 minutes.
Pour in pie shell and top with whipped cream and chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork
chops
in
skillet.
Place in casserole and cover with
sauerkraut.
Add
apples which have been pared and sliced. Sprinkle with
brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: yummy fruit salad
directions: In
large salad bowl mix undrained pineapple chunks and instant
pudding;
mix well.
Add other ingredients and blend. Chill.
(Bananas may be added just before serving.)

title: onion garlic dip
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, mix cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream dressing, onion, parsley and garlic.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Beat eggs until light. Add salad oil and mix in buttermilk, sugar and vanilla. Add pineapple, carrots, coconut, nuts and dry ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: patsy's fried pies
directions: Beat egg yolks with small amount of the milk, then combine. Combine flour, cornstarch and sugar. Stir into milk and egg mixture. Add coconut. Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles. Then add oleo and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell, then cover with Meringue.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix with mixer.
Can also be made into cheese ball and rolled in chopped nuts; however, if making cheese ball, use only one container of cheese spread.

title: vegetable quiche cups
directions: Microwave the spinach for 2 1/2 minutes on high. Drain the excess liquid. Line a 12 cup muffin pan with foil baking cups. Spray the cups with cooking spray. Combine the egg substitute, cheese, peppers, onions and spinach in a bowl. Mix well. Divide evenly among the muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Quiche cups can be frozen and reheated in the microwave. Any combination of appropriate vegetables and reduced fat cheese may be used. This has 3 grams carbohydrate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; top with mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Mix cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste and cornstarch; pour mixture over vegetables.
Mix together flour, milk and butter.
This batter will be slightly thin so you can spoon it and spread it over the top of the pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter until fluffy; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
In another bowl, combine oats and baking soda; add butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels; drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool and remove.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place everything in a casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: shrimp marinade
directions: Marinate shrimp for 3 hours in refrigerator and 10 minutes at room temperature before grilling.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and peppers and set aside.
Dice and cook potatoes on stove or in microwave until tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: butter rum cake
directions: Flour all nuts and fruits before mixing with other ingredients.
Mix butter and sugar first.
Add eggs, then other ingredients as listed.
(You may want to mix the baking powder with the flour before mixing with all other ingredients.)
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan (may use Baker's Joy to spray pan instead of greased and floured).
Let set overnight.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours with a pan of water underneath cake.
(This is real good.
It could be used as a fruit cake.)

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip the cream until stiff.
Slowly add salt and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder, add alternately with water.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to degree stated on cake mix box for tube or Bundt cake.
Grease pan with shortening.
Coat with flour.
Shake out excess flour.

title: corn medley casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown beef in large skillet.
Add salt, pepper, green pepper and onions; cook until onions are tender.
Stir in macaroni, corn, soup, sauce and chili powder.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and separate into bite-sized pieces.
Add onions and celery; simmer until tender.
Combine ground beef, onions and celery with remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased dish, 17 x 9 1/4-inch at 350° for one hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients until it turns golden brown.
Take off of stove.
Add a heaping tablespoonful of soda.
Stir real fast.
Pour out and let cool.

title: meat loaf special
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine crackers, steak sauce, mustard, catsup and eggs.
Mix well and add onion, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Make into a loaf; place in greased loaf pan.
Top with catsup and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and set for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frey's famous fried fowl
directions: Place ingredients in saucepan and heat until margarine is melted.
Baste chicken 3 to 4 times each side as you grill.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes (unpeeled), until tender.
Cool, peel and cube. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt, combined cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and garlic, which has been crushed thoroughly with the rest of salt (use less salt if you want to).
Fold in potatoes and pour in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, until browned on top.

title: north dakota monster cookies
directions: Mix together. Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli just until thawed.
Mix all ingredients (except stuffing) together in a large bowl.
Place in greased baking dish and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: simply delicious roast
directions: Mix onion soup mix with appropriate amount of hot water. Place roast in pan and pour onion soup and water mixture over roast leaving onion bits on top of roast.
Cover pan with foil. Bake at 225° for 1 hour per pound of meat.
The au jus can be mixed with corn starch to make a great gravy.

title: kings favorite bars
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and flour and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well, except chocolate chips, and spread over crust.
Put the chocolate chips on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.

title: creamy strawberry pie
directions: Follow baking directions on package of prepared pie crust. Mix yogurt, whipped topping and frozen sliced strawberries to taste.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and freeze.
Let thaw briefly before serving.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Combine fruits, marshmallows and coconut. Stir in sour cream and chill several hours or overnight.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Layer potatoes in dish, then layer half the package of sausage. In a bowl, mix together the green beans, mushrooms, onions, bell peppers, and pimentos.
Pour all of this over the potatoes and sausages, then layer all the remaining sausage.
Cover with foil and cook 1 hour at 400°.
Cover with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato snowballs
directions: Drain syrup off sweet potatoes.
Mash potatoes and mix together with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Cover marshmallows with sweet potato mixture; roll in coconut.
Arrange in buttered baking dish and bake at 450° until marshmallows are slightly softened.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top of bread.
Beat eggs with milk and pour in pan over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray iron skilled with Pam and 1/4 c. oil.
Put skillet in oven.
Place in bowl and mix well:
3 eggs and 1/4 c. oil.
Add sugar and baking soda.
Add 2 heaping c. self-rising cornmeal to mixture.
Pour enough buttermilk** in meal mixture until really "soupy."
(Take skillet out of oven and test to make sure grease is hot by placing a drop of cold water in skillet and see if it bounces.)
Add mixture to hot grease quickly.
Bake for 15-20 minutes.

title: peach crisp(yield: 100 servings)
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
Arrange fruit in 2 greased pans (18 x 26-inch sheet pans).
Pour 3 cups of juice over fruit in each pan.
Combine sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Stir lightly to moisten flour mixture.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, rolled oats and brown sugar until blended.
Add butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle 2 1/2 quarts of mixture over fruit in each pan. Bake 40 minutes at 375° or until browned.
Cut each pan 6 x 9-inches.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate the cauliflower buds; soak in cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Toss all ingredients together lightly and serve.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and oil in saucepan.
Warm until sauce is clear.
Place wings in sauce and cook until meat is tender (sauce should cover meat while cooking).
Also, works well with pork or beef ribs.

title: tropical storm
directions: In a blender container, combine the pineapple juice concentrate, water, milk, yogurt, sugar, vanilla and, if desired, banana.
Blend until smooth.
With blender running, add ice cubes slowly through the opening in the lid and blend until slushy.
Pour into glasses and garnish with pineapple chunks, if desired.
Makes 6 (4 ounce) servings.

title: crab meat mousse or mold
directions: Heat
together	until
smooth:	soup,
cream cheese and onion. Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add celery, mayonnaise and crab meat.
Add heated ingredients to gelatin mixture.
Spray or butter 2 quart mold.
Put	mixture
in mold and chill until set, 8 hours. Unmold; serve with crackers.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes or longer.
Roll thin.
Deep fat fry.

title: shrimp creole
directions: If using canned shrimp, rinse in cold water and drain.
Make sauce:
Cook onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes; stir in flour, cook until bubbly.
Add tomato sauce, salt, MSG, pepper and either bay leaf or dried basil.
Cook about 10 minutes, toss in shrimp, bring sauce to boil, then simmer 5 minutes until shrimp are heated through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.
(To prepare in a casserole:
Place shrimp in buttered casserole, add sauce, mix well.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: parmesan potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish or round 9-inch pie plate, melt butter in oven.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, coating with butter mixture.
Cover dish with foil; bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Continue baking, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are crisply tender.
Sprinkle with red pepper and parsley before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: skillet steak and corn
directions: In a skillet or wok over medium-high heat, brown steak, onion and thyme in oil.
Add broth; simmer for 10 minutes or until the liquid has evaporated.
Stir in tomatoes; cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Add the corn and heat through. Serve over rice.

title: rice pudding
directions: To the cooked rice, add all ingredients to one pot and let come to a boil.
Keep stirring all the time.
After it comes to a boil, shut off burner and remove from heat.
Add raisins.
Pudding will seem thin.
Don't worry, it will thicken upon standing. Cool for 1/2 hour.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Mix and fry until brown on both sides.
Serve with butter and honey or syrup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar, eggs, and zucchini together.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour 1/2 mixture into each pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loafs.

title: graham bars
directions: Line a large pan with broken graham crackers.
Boil butter, margarine, white sugar and vanilla for 4 minutes.
Spread hot mixture over crackers evenly, then sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Break up and store in a tight container.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Chop onion, pickles and olives very fine or chop in food processor.
Squeeze off juices.
Add mayonnaise and stir.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Mix
well
and
pack down in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: warm crabmeat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add the crabmeat and sour cream to taste.
Serve warm with chips.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook potatoes and onions in boiling water until tender.
Mash and return to water they were cooked in. Scald milk.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper to potatoes. Reheat and serve hot.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Place broccoli and onion in 4 cups of water.
Boil; add soups and turn heat to low.
Stir occasionally.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: one crust apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fill pastry crust with sliced apples. Combine dry ingredients and put over apples.
Pour the light cream over the apples and other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour, covered with foil; uncover and bake 30 minutes more or until apples are tender.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Place artichokes on bottom of casserole pan.
Squeeze moisture from spinach and layer on top of artichokes.
In mixer, blend cream cheese, mayo and butter until fluffy.
Gradually add milk; spread this over top of spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: lasagna italiano
directions: Combine 1/2 cup water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, ground beef, onion, mushrooms, oregano, basil and garlic powder in a large saucepan and simmer, uncovered, on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: mrs. goolsby's bride salad
directions: Combine and cool boiling water, sugar and Jell-O.
Mix together cottage cheese, pecans, pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: hot chicken loaf
directions: Place chicken in large kettle.
Add carrots, onion, celery, clove, peppercorn and salt.
Cover with cold water and simmer until tender, about 2 hours.
Strain stock and let chicken cool in stock.
When cold, drain, saving stock.
Discard skin of chicken. Remove meat and bones and dice meat.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour and sugar.
Cut in oleo with pastry blender until crumbly.
Place 1/2 mixture in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix the rhubarb, flour, sugar, cinnamon, water and salt; place this rhubarb mixture in pan.
Top with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: triple ginger cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and molasses until combined.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, and ground ginger.
Stir into butter mixture.
Stir gingerroot and crystallized ginger into batter.

title: butterfinger homemade ice cream
directions: Separate and beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks and mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Fill freezer with milk.
Process as usual.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cut oleo and flour with pastry blender and add nuts.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and bake for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: carrot and potato pudding
directions: Mix together, put in pan with holes in bottom.
Steam 1 hour or until done.

title: sharon's shower shrimp dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream and spread on bottom of meat platter.
Then layer in order:
shrimp, sauce, cheeses, pepper, scallions and tomato.
Cover with Saran Wrap before you put in refrigerator.
Refrigerate overnight and serve with crackers. Delicious!

title: sausage bisquick balls
directions: Mix ingredients; form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
These can be prepared ahead of time and reheated.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry orange gelatin over cottage cheese mixture.
Stir and let set five minutes.
Fold in coconut and add whipped topping.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: banana all-bran bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add All-Bran.
Mix well.
Add egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas, water and vanilla. Add nuts.
Allow to stand 1/2 hour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add soup, pimento and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Layer with rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla until blended.
Add coffee, cake mix and instant pudding; mix at medium speed until blended.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Fill hollowed pumpernickel bread (cut into cubes) with sour cream, Miracle Whip, soup mix and dried beef (mixed together). Place on platter with cubed bread, chips, etc., around outside.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in 6 cups of water and remove from broth. Remove chicken from bones, dice and return to broth. Add all ingredients except noodles. Boil for 1/2 hour. Add noodles. Boil for additional 7 to 10 minutes.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then slice.
Layer 1/3 potatoes in a greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Layer 1/3 bacon on top of potatoes, followed by 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: tea time macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy; add sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in softened peanut butter. Drop by rounded teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 dozen.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of shortening; brown stew meat.
Add salt, tomato soup and water.
Cook until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Let stand 1/2 day or until cool.
When mixing, mix 1 cup syrup with 4 cups of water.
Keep syrup in refrigerator.

title: meatball oven dinner
directions: Combine meat, onion, bell pepper, meal, seasonings, milk and egg.
Form into 12 meat balls.
Sprinkle with flour; brown in hot oil.
Place in large casserole.
To oil in skillet, add remaining flour; blend and add tomato juice.
Cook until medium thick; pour over meat balls.
Arrange vegetables around meat balls.
Sprinkle with salt; cover.
Bake 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onions.
Combine with chili powder, salt, pepper and cheese.
Keep a little cheese out to sprinkle on the top before cooking.
Spoon enough mixture on each tortilla to cover a third of it.

Roll tortilla, beginning at the filled edge. Place seam side down in a baking dish treated with nonstick spray. When tortillas are completed, combine soup, sour cream and green chilies to make a sauce.
Pour over tortillas.
Cover dish with foil and freeze with bag of cheese taped to it.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
The last 10 minutes sprinkle cheese on top.

title: shrimp cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart micro-proof casserole. Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes or until warm, stirring once during cooking time.
Stir.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Makes 2 cups. Cooking Time:
2 to 3 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except soda in a glass casserole dish. Microwave on high 1 minute; stir.
Microwave on high 1 1/2-2 minutes.
Stir in soda.

title: grilled chicken breasts caribbean
directions: Combine brown sugar and next 5 ingredients.
Pour marinade over chicken. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator 12 to 24 hours, turning once or twice.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade. Simmer marinade over medium-high heat until reduced by half, to about 3/4 cup.

title: cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake.

title: sweet-sour slaw
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, dissolve sugar in vinegar and water.
Add egg and cook slowly until mixture thickens (5 to 10 minutes).
Toss with cabbage and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: barbara's lemon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan; stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute while continuing to stir; this is very important to boil for entire minute.
Stir at least half of the hot mixture into the egg yolks very gradually.
Add to the remainder of the hot mixture in the saucepan.
Boil and stir for 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in margarine, lemon peel, lemon juice and food coloring, if you're using it.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Over low heat, combine and melt 1/3 cup milk and caramels.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, mix cake mix, butter and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Add nuts.
Stir by hand (dough will be stiff).

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans nearly done and put in cloth bag; put in stone jar. Mix all 4 ingredients and let solution come to a boil.
Remove and let cool before pouring over beans.
Let stand for 1 week or 10 days.
Take beans out of solution and wash.
Pack in glass jars and fill with cold water; process 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
If you have a 5 gallon jar, it will take 1 1/2 times the amount of solution.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar and beaten egg yolks in top of double boiler for 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice; add this mixture to well beaten egg whites.
Whip the cream and blend with other mixture.
Put one-half crushed crumbs in bottom of tray.
Pour in mixture, then sprinkle the rest of the crumbs on top and freeze hard until ready to serve.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer crumbs on bottom of pan.
Mix pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip and beat until smooth.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crumbs.
Add another layer of crumbs.
Spread frosting over other layer of crumbs.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: barbecue stew
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat. Mix all ingredients and cook overnight in crock-pot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer toast onto greased baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over toast.
Mix eggs, mustard and milk; pour over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Chill a bowl and rotary beaters.
Mix together in a saucepan the eggs, sugar, lemon juice, salt and reserved pineapple syrup. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Cool.

title: american enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients well, except cheese and onion.
Bake on hot griddle.
When done, sprinkle cheese and onion between pancakes, then pour sauce over them.

title: baked apples
directions: Place apples in greased casserole dish.
Mix sugar and spices; sprinkle over apples.
Add lemon juice.
Pour water over apples. Bake at 375° until done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger a little; drain.
Stir in potatoes, soup and salt.
Crumble and sprinkle onion rings on top.

title: pineapple mold and cranberries
directions: Wash cranberries, picking off any stems.
In a heavy saucepan, combine cranberries, water, sugar, cinnamon, allspice and pineapple and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to moderate boil; cook, stirring constantly, for about 10 to 12 minutes, until mixture is thick.
Pour into a 4-cup mold, rinsed with cold water.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or longer.
To release, dip bottom briefly in hot water and invert over serving plate. Garnish with fruit slice or pecan halves.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute finely minced onions, garlic and parsley in margarine until soft; do not brown.
Add tomato paste; stir well and cook for a few minutes.
Add shrimp and seasonings.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Thicken slightly with a little flour or cornstarch.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain; place broccoli in baking dish.
Combine soup and cheese; add milk, mayo and egg.
Stir until blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine margarine and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: piquant meat balls
directions: Mix well beef, breadcrumbs, egg and parsley.
Form into bite-size balls.
Set aside.

title: apricot jello
directions: Dissolve apricot Jell-O in crushed pineapple.
Heat till almost boiling.
Cool.
Add 2 cups of buttermilk.
Fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip and chill.

title: pineapple-apricot ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill freezer to indicator line with milk.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Makes 6 quarts.

title: onna's taco dip
directions: Mix together the first 3 items with peppers.
Add peppers to taste, the more peppers, the hotter it is.
Spread mixture in the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Top with grated cheese, chopped green onions, sliced black olives and chopped tomatoes.
Dip with tostados.
Eat and enjoy.

title: snockered potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender.
Pour off water.
Add cheap whiskey to potatoes.
Soak until potatoes are well snockered, about 10 minutes.
Strain into separate container.
Throw potatoes out.
Drink snocker!!

title: upper moreland beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef in frying or baking pan until well done.
Stir frequently to prevent lumping.
(Keep hot.)

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla; stir in flour, soda and salt.
Mix in nuts and potato chips.
Drop and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add pineapple and cherries. In a small bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put half of the batter in tube pan.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Repeat with the rest of the batter; stir very well.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: mock boursin au poivre
directions: Blend cream cheese with garlic, caraway, basil, dill and chives.
Pat into round, flat shape on piece of wax paper. Sprinkle another piece of wax paper with lemon pepper.
Roll cheese mixture on all sides with lemon pepper.
Wrap and refrigerate a day or more in advance.
Can be served without pepper coating.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly using fork (do not overbeat eggs).
Add salt, sugar and vanilla.
Scald milk and add slowly while stirring.
Pour filling into uncooked pastry.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together.
Can be served in Flintstone bread or put in wonton wraps and fried.

title: potato cheese pie
directions: Prehat oven to 375°.
Boil potatoes in jackets until tender. Peel and fore through ricer.
Add butter, milk, grated cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat until creamy and light.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine the rest of ingredients.
Mix both mixtures together.
Spoon into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I sprinkle this with cinnamon sugar before baking.

title: butterscotch sundae sauce
directions: Cook until a firm ball stage on candy thermometer (238°) the brown sugar, corn syrup and water.
Add melted margarine and marshmallows.
Allow to cool, then add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: knitting needle cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, and beat for two minutes.
Pour into oblong pan or tube.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Cook chocolate bar and 1 cup milk until thick or melted; cool. Beat well sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add chocolate and 1/2 milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done. If baked in cake pans, makes 3 small or 2 large pans or 10 x 12-inch pan.
Frost with either chocolate or butter frosting.

title: southwest supper chicken tostadas
directions: Heat tostada shells according to package directions.
In a medium skillet, quickly cook chicken strips and onion in butter until chicken is browned.
Add salsa
and remaining mix.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: cape briton oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oatmeal, soda, salt and sugar.
Rub in shortening. Use warm water to make dough stiff enough to roll on floured board.
Cut into squares.
Bake in slow oven until firm to touch.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Doritos and cheese.
Line bottom of pan with Doritos.
Pour mixture over Doritos.
Cover with Doritos and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Beat 10 minutes; add flour and milk alternately until blended.
Add flavoring.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil 1 pound of ziti; drain.
Boil broccoli; drain.
Cut chicken into small pieces (not too thin).
Saute garlic in vegetable oil until garlic is light brown.
Add chicken and saute for 5 minutes, then add cheese and peppercorns.
Add soup mix.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Stir until done.
Add broccoli and pour over ziti; mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and yolks.
Add milk and nuts and mix well.
Add enough flour until dough is thick enough to roll. Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick, then cut with cookie cutter. Bake in 350° to 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: lois' working girl batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients well. Spoon batter into greased muffin tins and bake 20 minutes at 450°.
This batter will keep in refrigerator.
Keep covered.

title: chicken swiss elegante
directions: Put chicken in shallow greased casserole.
Salt and pepper. Layer cheese atop chicken; mix soup and sherry and pour over all. Sprinkle stuffing over mixture; drizzle with margarine.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cheese potato soup casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Place potatoes in it.
Mix soup, sour cream, salt and pepper to 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour mixture over the potatoes and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: good and easy chocolate sauce
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together in saucepan.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Good warm over pound cake or ice cream or good served cold.

title: saucepan brownies(easy)
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients except eggs.
Mix and blend.
Add eggs and beat well. Grease a 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake. Frost, if desired.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in a saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, cook over medium heat, stirring, until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add carbonated beverage, orange and lemon juices.
Stir well to combine.
Chill until the consistency of egg whites.
Fold in fruit; spoon into an oiled 2-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Sift corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Beat egg lightly and add oil and milk. Add dry ingredients to liquid and stir well. Pour batter into muffin pans, approximately 2/3 full. Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add chocolate, milk and butter.
Let melt slowly.
When boiling, stir constantly exactly two minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until creamy.
One cup of nuts may be added with the vanilla, if desired.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan (greased).
Refrigerate when cool; cut into squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour scalded milk over dry bread pieces.
Let stand until soft.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, raisins and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: groovy green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Add salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Place in shallow baking dish and top with onion flakes and tomatoes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese or use Swiss or sharp Cheddar.
Place another can of green beans on top, mixed as at start.
Sprinkle with 2 more ounces cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put in 2 or 3 small greased loaf pans.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat egg. Add lemon and sugar. Cook into thick sauce, like pudding. Cool and add Cool Whip.

title: no roll pie crust(low-fat)
directions: Mix with fork in pie plate, then shape with hands to fit pie plate.
Remove a small portion and place on waxed paper and flatten for top crust.
After pie shell is filled with fruit, place waxed paper bottom side up over filling and carefully peel off, leaving pie crust in place.
Bake as any other pie.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Toss until evenly coated; if more dressing is needed, use 1/2 plus 1/2 measurements.
Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: best meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar and butter.
Shape into balls.
Make a mixture of brown sugar and butter.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over meat balls.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and flour, in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend butter and flour and add to corn mixture.
Mix well, it will slightly thicken.
Remove from heat.
Serves 8.
Add garlic powder and Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: california ranger cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening and sugars.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add slowly to mixture.
Stir well.
By hand, fold in cereals, nuts and raisins. Form into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter and place on cookie sheet.
Press slightly with a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: northern bean soup with ham
directions: In a large pot, add all of the ingredients and bring to a boil. Then let simmer for a couple of hours, stirring occasionally or until beans are tender.
Then add 3 cups of diced potatoes (this is optional).

title: sausage pineapple skillet
directions: Brown sausages and pour off all but 1 tablespoon grease. Brown chopped onions.
Separate pineapple chunks and juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.
Add all but rice and bring to a boil.
Add rice and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, covered. Serves 3 to 4.

title: italian sausage pasta soup
directions: Place sausage links in a large saucepan or 5-quart Dutch oven. Add water to a depth of about 1/2 inch; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until sausage is partially cooked; drain.
Cut sausage into slices.
Return to saucepan.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato sauce, basil and oregano; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables and pasta.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Cook and drain sausage, immediately coat hot meat with flour. Stir in milk and cook to thickness desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot baked biscuits.

title: beef tenderloin with brandy cream
directions: Saute beef filets 4 minutes on each side in butter over medium heat.
Remove from pan.
Add shallots and mushrooms.
Saute until just limp.
Add brandy.
Reduce by half.
Add beef broth and heavy cream.
Bring to a rolling simmer.
When cream begins to thicken, about 7 minutes, add the meat.
Continue to cook for about 8 minutes longer.
Season to taste.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion.
Add meat, garlic, flour, salt, pepper, paprika and mushrooms.
Add soup and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and serve at once over toast or rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters. Mix white sugar and cinnamon. Roll biscuit pieces in sugar mixture.
Put pieces in well-greased Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Do not boil.
Pour over pieces in pan.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, can milk and sugar.
Beat again. Then add vanilla, salt, milk, beat again, then put into ice cream freezer, turn till it sets or is frozen.

title: biscuit top stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; stir in soup, pimento and wine.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Place in greased (with margarine) casserole dish.
Top with biscuits.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wilma's dirt dessert(kids love this one)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix the pudding and milk, then blend in the Cool Whip.
Combine the first 3 ingredients with the pudding mixture.
Crush the entire package of Oreo cookies.
Pour half of the crushed cookies into the bottom of a sterilized flowerpot.
Fill with the pudding mixture and top with leftover cookies.
Artificial flowers and gummy worms can be put in flowerpot for effect.

title: citrus party olives
directions: Stir together first 10 ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before serving.
Garnish with rosemary sprigs, if desired. Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain and add margarine, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
If too thick, add a little milk or cream of chicken soup.
Put into a casserole dish and top with crushed saltines and dot with butter. Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: tomato and artichoke bake
directions: Saute green onions in butter until tender.
Stir in artichoke hearts, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Add crushed pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator until hard and set.
Melt chocolate and paraffin and dip.

title: cheez whiz olive bites
directions: Mix cheez whiz, butter crisco, and flour.
Press this mixture around each olive and chill for 1 hour.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve hot.

title: waldorf astoria cake(red cake)
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Measure next 6 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and food coloring.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat 4 minutes.
Stir in vinegar and soda mix.
Do not beat, fold in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8 x 8-inch flower pot.

title: zucchini bread(muffins)
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
In a separate bowl mix next 5 ingredients.
Slowly add dry mixture to wet mixture.
Pour into lightly greased and floured bread pans.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour or for muffins cook at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread houses
directions: Make glue with confectioners sugar and milk.
Attach graham cracker squares to sides of milk carton for walls and to top to make slanted roof.
Use your imagination to decorate your cottage, much like the witch in Hansel and Gretel.
Tint glue green and cover ice cream cone for a tree.
Decorate with candies for a Christmas tree.

title: baklava
directions: Combine walnuts, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon in bowl; mix well.
Set aside.
Brush bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with butter.
Layer 8 sheets of phyllo, each brushed with butter, in prepared pan.
Spread half the walnut mixture over layers.
Top with 2 buttered phyllo sheets and remaining walnut mixture.
Layer 8 buttered phyllo sheets over top.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: 2-corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Beat eggs in bowl; add corn and onions.
Stir.
Add muffin mix; stir.
Pour in ungreased, 4-quart casserole.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hamburg-rice meal
directions: Cut up cabbage; cook and drain.
Cook rice.
Mix hamburg with salt and pepper and fry.
Mix everything together.
Put cheese on top.
Pour pasta sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and boil until thick and clear.
Add jello.
Cool, then add fresh sliced strawberries. Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: peachy parmesan chicken
directions: Pound chicken between wax paper until 1/8-inch thick.
Spread mustard on 1 side of chicken; top with Prosciutto.
Roll up chicken; secure with toothpicks.
Mix flour with tarragon.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken in flour mixture, then add egg, then dip in crumbs.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining butter and wine; drizzle over chicken.
Add peach slices and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve with juices.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend sugar and eggs.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients; add to the sugar mixture.
Fold in chopped nuts and apples.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, or until done.
This cake is delicious served warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
It will stay moist for days if kept covered.
Good with whipped topping, also.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil water, oleomargarine and raisins for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased coffee cans.

title: easy ham and cheese pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; trim crust from bread.
Butter bread; place in buttered pan, buttered side down (use 1/2 of the bread). Spread Cheddar, ham and mushrooms in layers over the bread.
Cover with second layer of bread, buttered side down.
Place grated Swiss on top.

title: fillets in lemon dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Place 2 fillets on the bottom of an oiled baking dish.
Spread dressing over fish and top with remaining 2 fillets.
Dust with paprika; dot with margarine and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Yield:
4 servings. Approximate calories/serving:

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans. Stir over heat and bring to a boil. Lower heat to medium and continue cooking. Stir constantly and do not let stick. Candy is done when mixture forms a firm ball when dropped into cool water. Remove candy mixture from stove and beat until candy thickens. Add pecans and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer and sprinkle cinnamon over.
Beat together remaining ingredients and heat. Pour over bread and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until set and light brown.

title: dessert fruit pizza
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
When thick, add cream cheese.
Cool and spread on crust.

title: cucumber cinnamon rings
directions: First Day: Peel cucumbers and dig out centers. Cut in 1/4-inch rings. Place in glass or enamel container. Mix lime and water and cover cucumbers. Let stand overnight.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Mix sugar, spices and apple juice in a deep 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish.
Stir in cranberries and apples. Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until cranberries pop.
Uncover; microwave 2 to 3 minutes more until slightly thickened.
Stir in walnuts.
Let cool before serving.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix the whipped cream and cream cheese together.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle coconut over mix.
Top with sliced almonds. Pop into oven just long enough to toast the almonds.
Take out of oven and pour caramel over top of pie.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually work in dry ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham and pork together.
Add eggs, crumbs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Mold into a loaf and place in pan.
Do not cover to bake.

title: irish chili
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add chop meat and brown. Drain fat from meat and discard.
Add pinto beans and juices from can.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Place in 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Place shredded Cheddar cheese on top of meat.
Place potatoes on top of cheese. Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4. Great for leftover chop meat and/or potatoes.

title: shortcake(served with any type of berry)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into medium mixing bowl.
Rubbing between fingers, or cutting with crossed knives or pastry cutter, work butter into dry ingredients until mixture forms consistency of cornmeal, with few larger lumps of butter left intact.
Add half of the cream and stir into dry ingredients with fork.
Add remainder of cream, bit by bit, until mass forms that pulls cleanly away from bottom and sides of bowl.

title: overnight layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce.
Place in bottom of pan.
Add in layers the onion and peas.
Combine the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Spread over peas.
Sprinkle sugar on sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add layer of grated cheese next.
Top with bacon pieces.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 8 to 24 hours before serving.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter in a slow cooker.
Add cheese and melt.
Add tomatoes and chopped peppers.
Heat and serve with chips or crackers.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss and mix well.
Refrigerate. Will keep 4 to 5 days.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat in oil until it is no longer red. Add onions, water, tomatoes, and tomato sauce. Cook for about one hour. Then add spices and cook for about 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers or whatever you choose.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Scoop out and dice.
Saute in 4 tablespoons butter and cook until tender, stirring often and reserve.
Melt remaining butter (2 tablespoons).
Cook onion for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Combine mushroom mixture, eggplant, 1/2 package cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
May be baked in the eggplant shell.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Add meat and mix well. Shape into loaf in shallow pan or pack into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients seasoning with garlic salt, pepper and salt. Additional mayonnaise can be added if necessary. Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced okra
directions: Combine water, onion, garlic, cayenne, white pepper and salt. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Add okra and cook briskly, gently stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes or until almost all of the liquid in the pan has evaporated and okra is tender, but intact.
Take the okra out of pan and put into a colander.
Run cold water over it to set the color and stop the cooking.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Drop by spoonful on filling.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with milk.

title: quick pasta fagoli
directions: In a saucepan saute onion in heated olive oil until onion is soft and translucent.
Add cannellini beans and 1/2 can water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
In separate pot cook tubettini.
Drain and add to sauce.
Garnish with grated cheese.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage (use candy thermometer).
Add nuts.
Stir until sugar starts to harden. Pour onto wax paper or foil to cool.
Separate into bite size pieces.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring spoons, etc.
Check the rum again. It must be of the highest quality.
Pour 1 (one) level cup of rum in a glass and drink it.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat the butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of tugar and beat again.
Check the rum for its quality again.
Try another cup. Open the second quart.
Add the two (2) arge leggs, 2 cup fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in the beaters, just pry loose with a drewscriver.
Next, sift 3 cups baking powder, a pinch of rum, a seaspoon of toda and a cup of salt or pepper (it really doesn't matter).
Sample rum.
Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 bablespoon of borwn sugar or whatever color you can find.
Wix mell.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350 gredees.
Now, pour the whole mess into the oven.
Perhaps it would be better to forget the coven and the rake.
Just check the rum again and bo to bed.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour spaghetti and sauce in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix in hamburger/onion.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, milk and chocolate morsels in a 1 quart glass bowl or mixing cup.
Microwave at Medium-high (70% power) for 4 to 5 minutes until chocolate melts, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream.

title: applesauce bran cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and soda.
Mix together the margarine and egg until fluffy.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, then add the applesauce.
Mix well. Fold in the raisins and all-bran.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Great for diabetics.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender.
Add salt and other ingredients.
Simmer until creamy.
Serves 6.

title: "make your own" sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in the container of the electric blender.
Process
until
smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready for use.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Slightly flatten each chicken breast.
Place in baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli 5 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli in a casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with wooden spoon or potato masher in medium size bowl.
Add brown sugar and melted butter.
Shape 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mixture around one large marshmallow.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Place sweet potato balls on
ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350 degree oven for 12-15 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with low-fat Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
tags: cream of celery soup with small amount skim milk

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand a few minutes.
Cool boiling water to lukewarm; add eggs.
Add yeast and stir well.
Add flour.
Add sugar.
Knead on well floured board.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll out.
Pour butter on dough.
Roll like
a jellyroll. Slice into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin tins and let rise in warm place slowly.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chicken drummettes
directions: Place drummettes evenly in shallow pan.
Pour soy sauce over chicken and bake at 200° for 6 hours.
Drain well and serve while hot.

title: tortilla wedges
directions: Mix all and spread thinly on each tortilla making layers until mixture is gone.
Top with one last tortilla and chill.
Cut into small wedges and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together first two ingredients and set aside.
Boil together next four ingredients and, while still hot, pour over first batch.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: pecan cupcakes
directions: Melt together oleo, chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix together flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures, mixing well.
Fill cupcake paper cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Needs no frosting.

title: corn souffle or pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt with corn.
Add melted oleo and milk.
Beat yolks and add to mixture.
Beat whites until "stiff" and fold into the mix.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Cream margarine. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Shape like dates or crescents and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm. Cool, then roll in sugar again.

title: chocolate zucchini brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: very fine chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ham puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolk, baking powder and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Cut bread in fourths.
Spread each piece with mayonnaise.
Spread each with small amount of ham.
Spoon on cheese mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Put in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Serve.
Makes about 45 appetizers.
May be frozen.

title: pepper and tomato dish
directions: Cut up onion and fry in bacon fat until tender and slightly brown.
Slice peppers in strips.
Add to onion and fry until tender.
Add cut up tomatoes; simmer until tender.
Season with salt.
Can be served with meat or cold as a sandwich spread.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with second pie crust.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Let cool before slicing.

title: chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Add half of dried beef, chopped onions and spices.
Shape into ball and add remaining beef to outside of ball.
Chill thoroughly.

title: any flavor cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to instructions on box.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Bake according to box instructions.
Top with whip cream.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Trim crust off bread and butter bread generously; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Mix bread cubes and cheese in baking dish.
Put bacon over cheese and bread.
Add eggs, beaten with milk and salt; pour over top of bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake (at least) 50 minutes at 350°.
You may add parsley or mushrooms before baking.
Sausage may be substituted for bacon.
When you bake, it will rise up, fill the pan and be very fluffy.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Mix all together.
Turn out dough on well-floured board and knead well.
Add flour to make stiff.
Roll out very thin.
Cut with scalloped pie pan, place in a 9-inch round cake pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: billy's tater tot and chili casserole
directions: Bottom layer:
chili.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheeses on top of chili. Top with Tater Tots.
Cook in oven according to Tot directions. Top with remaining cheeses.
Serve hot.

title: easy, easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour icing over cake while hot.
This cake is so easy, no beating, no messy bowls to wash, it's all made in the pan.

title: easy chicken supper
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of baking pan.
Cover with chicken, skin side up.
Pour on melted butter.
Season to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in buttered 9 x 15-inch rectangular pan. Mix 1 cup water and 1 cup soup.
Mix and combine with milk and water. Pour over rice. Salt and pepper chicken.
Place over mixture. Top with dots of butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours or until lightly browned and rice is cooked.

title: wisconsin cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in 1/2 inch deep boiling water 10 to 12 minutes until fork-tender.
Cool slightly; peel and shred.
(Can do earlier.)
Place combined potatoes, cheese and onion in buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Place thin pats of the butter on top.
Pour cream over surface.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until tender and golden.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rich and luscious cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Combine crumbs, sugar, and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9 inch spring form pan.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and all vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In small bowl, stir together milk and flour.
Add to soup mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook another minute.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in nutmeg.
Makes 4 servings, just 3 grams of fat each.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in deep pan.
Cover with water.
Add diced bacon, chopped onions and butter.
Saute mushrooms in small skillet with 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to soup.
Let cook over medium heat until potatoes are done.
Mix cornstarch and milk together, then pour into soup for thickening.
Salt and pepper.

title: favorite banana bread
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crab cocktail quiche
directions: Roll out pastry on floured surface. Cut into 2 3/4-inch circles with scallop-edged cutter. Fit circles into 1 3/4-inch mini muffin tin cups. Place bite-sized amount of crab in cup. Combine cream, eggs, cheese, lemon peel and seasonings; whisk to blend. Spoon egg mixture over crab. Fill cups about 3/4 full. Bake in 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and golden. Cool slightly before serving. Garnish tops with additional crabmeat and fresh dill. Yield: 24 appetizers.

title: e-z peach pie
directions: Melt butter in glass bowl.
Mix sugar and flour together. Stir in milk.
Pour liquid into hot butter, then add peaches. (You can use any kind of fruit.)
Let cook until pie is brown on top.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Cook chuck roast in oven at 250° for 7 to 8 hours or in crock-pot until tender.
Separate and shred cooked meat.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add meat and heat thoroughly.
Serve on semi-hard rolls.
Makes 1 dozen.
Double recipe for 2 or more roasts.

title: jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add 3/4 cup sugar to peaches; heat.
Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next add the dough and then the peaches on top.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Cut onion and corned beef into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients into casserole dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve warm on crackers.
A good cracker is Breton wheat cracker.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in a pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: ol' fashion sugar cookies
directions: Beat together oil and margarine. Beat in granulated sugar. Beat in powdered sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend in vanilla. Blend in mixed dry ingredients. Chill, overnight is best. Roll into small balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until very light brown. Cookies are rich.
If using no stick sheets, no greasing is necessary.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Add boiling water with baking soda to dates and let cool. Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add date mixture to it; then add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large pot, bring water to boil; add salt and macaroni. Boil 8 to 10 minutes; drain (DO NOT RINSE).

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass buttered and dipped in sugar.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onions until beef is browned; drain.
In greased 9 x 13-inch dish, spread refried beans. Sprinkle beef mixture over beans.
Add layers of olives (reserving some for garnish), chilies and cheese.
Spread taco sauce all over. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread sour cream over casserole and garnish.
Serve with nacho chips.
Add lettuce and tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Simmer meat 4 or 5 hours, until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from liquid.
Remove any bone or fat.
Shred meat; return to liquid.
Serve on sourdough rolls.
Fresh or canned mushrooms may also be added.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes about 1 pint of dressing.

title: delicious pecan pie
directions: Mix well corn syrup, sugar, salt, margarine and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into pie shell and sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: empire biscuits
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Mix flour, sugar and egg until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prize winning chili
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet and drain.
Add onions, green peppers, celery, garlic, chili peppers, bay leaf.
Cook 8-10 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, paste, sauce, and beans.
Cover just to the top with water.
Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
When serving, top with finely shredded sharp cheddar cheese.
Serves 6-8.

title: chocolate whoopie pie cake
directions: Grease 2 large sheet cake pans and line with wax paper. Divide cake batter evenly into the two pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and warm water.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Add liquid and mix well. Refrigerate.
Pinch off as needed.
Bake at 475°.
No need to let rise.
Can bake in muffin tins or form into balls and place on pan.

title: chinese pork and vegetables
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. oil in wok or large skillet over medium high heat. Add peppers, radishes and onions; stir fry 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp tender. Add water chestnuts and mushrooms; stir fry for 1 minutes. Remove vegetables from pan. Add remaining oil and pork to pan; stir fry 9 to 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in vegetables and all remaining ingredients except rice; simmer 1 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: vegetable tacos
directions: In a large bowl, add jicama, purple cabbage, carrots, chopped broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes and Italian dressing.
Mix well. In a flat pan filled with Crisco oil, dip corn tortillas until soft.
Dab with a paper towel to get rid of excess grease.
Layer folded tortillas with beans, avocado, vegetable mixture, sprouts and top with Jack cheese.
Preheat beans.
Serve with white rice.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and garlic salt. Beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Using a teaspoon, drop batter into 1/8-inch hot oil in a frying pan. Cook for 3 minutes until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper. Serves 6.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cook
over
medium
heat to all-over boil.
Lower heat; continue stirring for 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add peanuts; stir
until mixture thickens.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 24 candies.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, syrup, cream of tartar, salt and margarine to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla and beat down.
Pour over popped corn and stir to coat corn. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with Pam. Brown beef and onion in skillet over medium heat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mix well.
In small bowl, combine Mozzarella, cottage cheese and egg whites.
Mix well.
In prepared pan, spread 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 of rice and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining meat sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potato cheese casserole
directions: Beat soup and milk together until smooth.
Add layer of potatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour soup mixture over each potato layer in a quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 1 hour covered and 15 minutes longer without cover.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Break mincemeat into small pieces. Add water.
Boil 1 minute. Cool. Sift flour and soda together. Combine eggs, mincemeat, milk, fruit and nuts. Fold in dry ingredients.
Bake slowly until top springs back (in tube or small pan).
While still warm, glaze with orange marmalade.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and melted butter. Add other ingredients in order given, except pie filling, cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Spread with pie filling. Spread remainder of batter over filling. Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Put all ingredients into medium bowl.
Mix well.
Chill about 1 hour.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.
Also good with chips or crackers.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 3 hours.
Serve over egg noodles, cooked.

title: popcorn surprise
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Stir in popcorn and peanuts. Let cool a few minutes.
Stir in M&M's.
Press onto a cookie sheet.

title: soft dutch cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, Crisco, butter and sugar.
Mix until crumbly.
With spoon, mix in eggs and milk.
Put batter into 2 greased pie pans, which are sprayed with Pam.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian macaroons
directions: Work the almond paste with your hands, then proceed to add sugar and egg whites; constantly knead. Now, add flour and powdered sugar to the paste. Line aluminum foil on your cookie sheet. Drop 1/2 teaspoon on your cookie sheet and wait 24 hours until the curing is complete. Now, bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Decorate each cookie with a bright red cherry.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: mom's tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger; add tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic salt, onion and green pepper.
Mix; set aside.
In saucepan, cook until very thick the cornmeal and water.
Pour 1/2 cornmeal in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add hamburger and corn, then the rest of cornmeal on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Add beans, picante sauce and taco seasonings mix.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into 12 x 8 x2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour and bake in melted butter for 30 minutes at 425°.
Turn after the first 15 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Turn the temperature down to 325°.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, peanut butter, egg and vanilla together in bowl.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: elephant stew(an old family recipe)
directions: A half a cup of friendship and a cup of thoughtfulness.
Cream together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, very lightly, beaten in a bowl of loyalty.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars. Add 1 hot pepper to each jar, if desired.
Add fresh dill into jars (1 good size sprig per jar). Bring salt, water and vinegar to rolling boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens. Cook 2 minutes longer. Remove. Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks; return to hot mixture; cook 2 minutes; stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour into prepared pastry shells. Cool to room temperature.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until soft ball stage the first 3 ingredients.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Get peanut butter stirred in before adding marshmallow cream.
Put in buttered pan. Cool and cut into small squares.

title: cream cheese clam dip
directions: Stir milk into cream cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, peppers and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in clams. Sprinkle paprika.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch flat casserole with Pam, then begin to layer:

spaghetti, pour melted margarine over, then tomato sauce, spices, garlic, salt and pepper, 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 pound Swiss. Add green pepper, onion, sausage, pepperoni and mushrooms. Cover with 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 pound Swiss cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly and cheeses are melted thoroughly.
Let set 5 minutes.
This freezes beautifully. Be sure to
use full amount of cheese. Serves 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine altogether; mix well.
Let stand at least 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.
May add any other fruit, to salad, desired

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Add carrots and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chili powder, salt, catsup and beer; stir 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and juice; cook low for 1 hour.
Add beans and cook 1/2 hour longer.
