Cooked elbow macaroni may be added after cooking for Chili Mac and topped with Cheddar cheese slices.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, soda, flour, spices and salt together in a bowl. Add eggs, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Stir until mixed (will be thick).

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vanilla to milk. Stir sifted ingredients into butter mixture alternately with milk and bananas.
Beat batter until smooth after each addition.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch cake pans in moderate 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place sliced bananas between layers.
Ice top of cake with uncooked lemon icing.

title: kyle's quick and easy chili
directions: Cook beef and onion in Dutch oven until browned; drain.
Add tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 9 cups.

title: mrs. tom curtis' spoon bread
directions: Warm milk.
Slowly pour corn meal into milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add butter and salt. Beat and cool.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(A souffle-like bread served in place of potatoes.
Serve with butter or gravy.)

title: delicious simple dressing
directions: Toast bread, cut into cubes.
Combine celery, onion and seasonings.
Bring broth to a boil and add to bread and celery. Add eggs last and stir well.
Put into casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to
boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Combine broccoli and remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add vinegar mixture.
Toss. Pack into 4 (1-pint) freezer containers, filling to 1/2-inch from top.
Cover, label and freeze up to one month.
To serve, thaw in refrigerator 8 hours.
Yields 8 cups.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or a glass. Brush top with melted butter and bake at 425° until done.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and brown in a large skillet over medium heat.
Sprinkle with chili mix.
Add rice, water and tomatoes.
Be sure all rice is moistened.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin leather
directions: Blend ingredients well and dry in dehydrator or oven.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears and drain.
Grind peppers and onions.
Put pickling spice into cheese cloth and remove after cooking.
Cook approximately 40 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Bring the sugar, Pet milk, water and butter to a boil.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add the pecans and vanilla.
Beat until glossy. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, buttermilk, egg and shortening thoroughly, then add your pork cracklings.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake until brown. (Bake in skillet.)

title: pat's honey mustard
directions: Combine all together.
Blend/mix until smooth and creamy. Store in the refrigerator.
Serve warm or cold.
Use as a dip for vegetables.
Use as a salad dressing.
Pour a little on each bite of your hamburger as you eat it.
Dip your French fries in it, etc., etc.

title: deep-dish chicken pie
directions: In bowl, combine biscuit mix and sage.
Prepare biscuit dough according to package directions for biscuits except substitute 1/4 cup of the chicken gravy for the liquid.
Roll out on waxed paper to an 8-inch circle.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine remaining gravy with mushrooms, olives and pepper.
Stir in chicken with its broth.
Bring to boil; turn into an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Invert dough onto hot sauce; remove paper.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° until done, 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken a la greque
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine oregano, salt and pepper in a small dish. Rub seasonings into chicken. Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Blend olive oil and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken pieces. Bake 40 minutes until tender.

title: oven hash browns
directions: Put hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine everything else. Put 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/2 cup melted butter on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp mousse mold
directions: Heat soup; soften gelatin in water and add to soup and dissolve.
Cut cheese and gradually add to soup, stirring; blend in mayonnaise.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Gel.

title: great dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pie plate. Sprinkle on diced onion and pepper. Cover with salsa, then Monterey Jack cheese. Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat all together until hot and serve.

title: hummus(a middle eastern dip)
directions: Drain beans.
Combine in food processor or blender with oil, lemon juice and garlic.
Process until smooth.
Vary consistency as desired with more or less oil or lemon juice.
Garnish with sesame oil or parsley.
Chill.
Serve with torn pieces of pita bread.

title: peanut cluster candy
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Stir in peanuts and spoon onto foil.
Let it cool until hard.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put spices in top of percolator.
Pour juice in bottom and let perk.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel and slice thinly.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Saute onions in bacon fat until golden brown. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in potatoes and bacon.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand before serving.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple juice.
Let it set slightly. Mix with Cool Whip.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Add pineapple and cherries, if desired.

title: baked pok chops 'n brown rice
directions: Put rice, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt 'n rosemary in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1 tablespoon buttah in big skillet.
Brown chops on both sides; set aside.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Spread in pan.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Layer crab meat.
Sprinkle on shrimp.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: beef potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; blend in flour.
Remove from heat.
Add onion, then stir in milk.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add beef, mushrooms with liquid, pepper to taste and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread potatoes in greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Pour beef mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Additional potatoes can be fluted around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: favorite jam cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter with spoon.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour; stir until blended.
Make small balls; dip in egg whites, then in chopped nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and press your finger in each cookie.
Return to oven and finish baking for 20 minutes.
While the cookies are still hot, put preserves in.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour, add gradually.
Bake in greased pan at 300° for 1 hour or until done when tested.

title: pumpkin date bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, oil, water and vanilla until blended.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture, stirring until just combined.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour mixture into four greased 7 x 3 x 2-inch baking pans or two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 55 minutes for smaller loaves; about 65 minutes for larger loaves or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool bread 10 minutes on wire racks.
Loosen sides; remove from pans.
Cool completely on rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 4 small or 2 large loaves.

title: orange date bars
directions: Combine dates, equal sugar, oil and orange rind in saucepan. Cook 5 min. to soften dates.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spread into an oiled 8x8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 min.
Cool before cutting.
Diabetic Food exchange:
1\2 starch plus 1\2 fat per bar.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine for a short time.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam or another spray.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts of vegetables on top of cream cheese.
roll tortillas tightly. chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1 in pieces.
Discard ends.
Serve with spirals facing up.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sweet potato apple bake
directions: *Variation:
Can substitute canned yams for sweet potatoes.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Mix water, cornmeal, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix together hot water, jello and cake mix and let cool. Then add oil, eggs and lemon flavoring.
Bake in cake pan or loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine together. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust. Mix gelatin, hot water and strawberries. Set aside to congeal lightly.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put piece of ham in a pot and boil for approximately 30 minutes.
Add all vegetables.
Cook over low heat for about 2 hours.
Fresh, frozen or canned vegetables can be used to make this soup.

title: reeses' peanut butter cups
directions: Melt Hershey bar.
Melt peanut butter in a glass bowl with water until pour able, separately.
Pour chocolate in cupcake pan, let set.
Add peanut butter, let set.
Add more chocolate and let stand.

title: sour kraut(goldies)
directions: Pack cabbage in jars.
Use water, vinegar and salt.
Mix and heat well.
Pour over kraut in jars and seal.

title: chocolate cookie dough with chocolate-covered cherries
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until dough forms, about 1 minute.
(Dough will be stiff.) Shape dough into 1-inch balls, using heaping teaspoon for each. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Push one cherry halfway in each ball.
When all are pushed in, prepare frosting mix.
Use immediately.
Frost each one by using 1/2 teaspoon of frosting for each one.
Frosting will spread some during baking. Bake frosted cookies at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until puffy.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix
cake
as
directed on package.
Grease and flour a large jelly
roll
pan.
Pour in cake batter and bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Cool.	Mix pudding with 1 cup milk.
Beat cream cheese into pudding mix.
Fold Cool Whip into cheese and pudding mixture.
Spread
on
cool cake.
Sprinkle pineapple, then cherries, nuts and coconut on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour over stuffing mix.
Cover with remaining mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: appalachian stack cake
directions: *Dried apples give the best flavor, but are scarce and must be soaked before cooking.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake in layer pans at 350° for approximately 25 to 35 minutes.

title: baked cheesy chili dip
directions: Microwave:
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring every 4 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan, mix well, and add egg yolks, lemon juice and water.
Beat with whisk until smooth. Place over medium heat, bring to boil, cook, stirring briskly, until clear and thickened.
Cook 5 minutes, then pour in baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: ozark hoecakes
directions: Mix all and stir in water to make a soft dough.
Make into small cakes and bake on hot, greased griddle.

title: italian lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, 3 cups water, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles.
Arrange in layers as follows:
Ground beef, cottage cheese, noodles and Mozzarella.
Continue making layers until ingredients are all used.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, sugar, baking powder, salt, buttermilk, eggs and peppers.
Add cream cheese and press into mix.
Bake in iron skillet at 350°.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Melt butter and add 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add water to the butter and cocoa; bring to a boil, then mix with the flour and sugar mixture.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost.

title: curry-tomato dipping sauce
directions: Puree tomatoes and their liquid in blender or food processor until smooth. Measure out 2 cups of the puree and scrape into medium-size bowl.
Reserve remainder for another use.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Heat chocolate and shortening in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, about 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; spread with Glossy Chocolate Frosting.

title: jello pie
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water in medium bowl; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Mix in ice cream until melted.
Pour in crushed pineapple and place in pie shell and refrigerate until filling is solid.

title: pickle dainty for party
directions: *Use Cates finger-size so bread will go all the way around.
tags: king-size loaf thin slice white bread

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and mix with other ingredients.
Bake until set real good.

title: oatmeal sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Shape rounded teaspoon into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass, dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken cheese macaroni
directions: Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 420° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Butter sides of casserole dish. Whip all ingredients, except paprika, together until smooth.
Pour into casserole dish and top with sprinkle of chives and paprika. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Eat!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place drained pineapple in a bowl.
Add sugar, flour and Cheddar cheese.
Stir.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down until even.
Crush 1 1/2 stacks of Ritz crackers over top.
Pour 1 stick margarine (melted) over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries; drain on paper towels, then slice.
Chill berries while cooking glaze.
Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add remaining ingredients (except Cool Whip) and cook until thick. Pout berries in crust; pour hot mixture over berries at once. Chill until jelled.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake on 350° for 20 minutes, then lower to 325° and cook until knife blade comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: rolled cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in
a
bowl; blend well.
Cover and chill in refrigerator
until
firm.
With your hands, roll batter into small balls,
then
roll each ball lengthwise into strips, thick in the middle
and
turned
down at ends to form crescent shape.
Bake on a cookie
sheet in a 375° oven for 15 minutes until
golden.
Cool.
Sprinkle
with
confectioners sugar and cinnamon.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: grandmother's applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce until bubbling.
Pour over shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Stir until shortening and sugar dissolve. Sift spices, salt and soda with flour.
Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan or loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato gourmet
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until done.
Cool and peel.
Then grate potatoes.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and cheese.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold into potatoes.
Bake in covered, greased dish for 25 minutes at 300°.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in 4 loaves.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ground beef teriyaki
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook onions, celery, carrot and pepper until tender-crisp, stirring often.
Remove vegetables to bowl.

title: stuffing and squash
directions: Slice squash thinly; cook and drain.
In a large mixing bowl, empty the box of stuffing and add the amount of water directed on the package.
Melt the margarine.
Add margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and squash to stuffing in bowl; mix together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled mayonnaise dressing
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
This will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: popcorn bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except popped corn, and cook slowly until the soft ball stage.
In large pan, pour cooked mixture over popped corn and mix fast.
Pour in pan lined with wax paper, if desired.
May be packed firmly and cut into bars.
I have made this each year for Christmas since 1945.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of dish. Layer next 7 ingredients in order.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt cheese and cream cheese together; add picante sauce and beef.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil all ingredients except soda and corn for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add soda.
Stir mixture well.
Pour over popped corn in baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir lightly every 15 minutes.
Can add peanuts or pecans.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Empty can of lemonade into container.
Fill can twice with orange juice.
Add 1/2 can of whiskey and sugar to taste.
Mix well and serve over ice.

title: mulligatawny
directions: In a large saucepan combine broth, chicken, undrained tomatoes, apple, onion, carrot, celery, green pepper, parsley, lemon juice, sugar, curry, ground cloves, salt and dash of pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken tetrivini
directions: Boil chicken with salt, pepper and garlic.
Debone.
Set aside. Use 3 cups of water that chicken was boiled in.
Add the celery, bell pepper, mushroom soup, chicken soup, onion and pimentos. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken, egg noodles and Velveeta cheese. Simmer 10 minutes more.
Put in casserole pan.
Cover with sliced Velveeta cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: doughnuts with apples
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time and beat after each.
Sift dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Add milk; cut apples in small pieces and add to dough mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fat heated to 375°.
Fry 3 minutes, turning once to brown all sides.
Drain, then roll in confectioners sugar or cinnamon sugar.

title: sausage pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil in heavy skillet until light brown. Slice sausage into rounds; add to skillet.
When brown, add can of tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper and dash of sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until fat is reduced.

title: salmon or tuna loaf
directions: Drain broth from fish and mushrooms into cup. Add water to make 1 cup. Place liquid in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add rice cereal and cook, stirring constantly.
Cover and let stand a few minutes.
Flake fish.
Add egg and cheese to cereal and stir until cheese melts.
Blend in fish, lemon juice and mushrooms. Spray Pam in loaf pan.
Spread fish mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out to platter.
Serves 4.

title: easy carbonara
directions: Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
In same pan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Add wine to drippings; boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Add milk, eggs and contents of seasoning packet; stir over low heat until sauce is desired consistency.
Toss with noodles and reserved bacon.

title: bacon and cheese waffles
directions: In a medium bowl, blend together egg, milk, sour cream and butter. Stir in biscuit baking mix; blend well. Mix in bacon and cheese. Pour in enough batter to fill a preheated waffle iron. Bake until waffle is crisp and golden. Makes 12 waffles.

title: janet's chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Yum Yum Good!

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, buttermilk and melted margarine by hand.
Add coconut.
Pour mixture in unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: no bean chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese to cover bottom of glass pie plate. Spread no bean chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 4 to 5 minutes on High or until cheese is all bubbly.
Serve hot with tortilla chips. Guaranteed to disappear!

title: extra good barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces.
Brown them in a baking pan over surface heat.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the ribs.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 1 3/4 hours.
Spoon the sauce over the meat 2 or 3 times during baking.
Bake uncovered an additional 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: eggnog quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, eggnog, margarine, rum extract and vanilla; blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased pan.

title: old fashioned pound cake(50 years old)
directions: Cream butter with oil.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour, salt and milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into patties and drop onto greased, hot griddle.
Brown on each side.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Brown together ground beef, garlic salt and onion.
Drain, put in crock-pot.
Add vegetables: Veg-All that has been drained, stewed tomatoes and okra.
Let simmer for 4 to 5 hours.

title: spring fling trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using milk.
Combine 1 1/2 cups strawberries and fruit spread in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.
Layer 1/3 of cake cubes in a 2 1/2-quart straight sided glass serving bowl.
Spoon 1/3 of the pie filling mixture plus 1/3 of strawberry puree over cake; top with 1/3 each of remaining strawberries, blueberries, peaches and banana.
Repeat layer twice. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Chop broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Prepare popcorn.
Place in well buttered bowl.
Combine in saucepan the sugar, syrup, water and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cook to hard ball stage. Pour syrup slowly over popcorn, mixing well.
With buttered hands, form into balls of desired size.

title: dorma's punch
directions: Mix and freeze. To serve, add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: venison roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form marinade and pour over roast.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 to 5 days, turning twice a day.
Remove meat and pat dry with a paper towel.
Strain marinade and reserve both marinade and vegetables.
Make deep slits and insert pieces of bacon or rinsed salt pork.

Melt 3 to 4 tablespoons fat in heavy roasting pan and brown meat evenly. Cover loosely with foil and roast in oven at 350° for 20 minutes per pound for medium and 30 minutes per pound for well done. Remove roast to a large platter and set on top burner.
Saute vegetables from marinade.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon and put around roast.
Stir in a little flour to make a brown roux, then stir in reserved marinade.
Cook until thickened. Correct seasoning and pour into a sauce boat.

title: beef brisket
directions: Make the night before:
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in a cooking bag.
Bake at 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Refrigerate. Cut in 1/2-inch slices, reheat and serve.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries, Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and freeze.

title: pull apart rolls
directions: *May substitute tubes of cinnamon rolls.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 1 minute; add sugar and lemon juice, beating well.
Add soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in flour and pumpkin until well blended.
Spread batter into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn cake out onto dish towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel until completely cooled.

title: pork chops with vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Brown the pork chops, 3 at a time, on both sides and remove them from the skillet.
Saute the green pepper for 1 minute; remove them.
Add flour to the skillet, blending well and cook for 1 minute.
Blend in the onion soup, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salt.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Return the chops to the skillet, basting them with sauce.
Cover and simmer until the chops are tender, about 1 hour.
Blend in the tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and form balls.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine (butter) in bowl and add cocoa, sugar, milk. Stir and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and rolled oats.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix in order given.
Place mixture in loaf pan. Top with tomato soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In medium skillet, combine drink mix powder, brown sugar, butter and water.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add potatoes; cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes, turning to glaze all sides of potatoes.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.

title: tortas de aceite(aniseed biscuits)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and grated lemon rind.
Make a well in the center and pour beaten egg, oil and anise.
Gradually stir all ingredients together to give a smooth, firm mixture.
Roll this out thinly and cut into small rounds.
Place on a greased baking tray and cook in a preheated hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
The number of biscuits will depend on how thinly the mixture is rolled.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish.
Flour chicken and add to dish.
Bake chicken, rib side up, for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from dish.
Add rice, onion and bell pepper to dish.
Then put chicken back on top of rice.
Mix chicken broth and soup together in saucepan over heat.
Pour over chicken and rice and bake until liquid is gone, 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: salmon burgers
directions: In medium bowl, combine salmon, eggs, 2/3 cup bread crumbs, the scallions, lemon juice and pepper until well-blended.
Shape into 4 patties, about 3/4-inch thick; coat with remaining 1/3 cup bread crumbs.
Place patties on wax paper lined plate; chill 1 hour.

title: spicy snack crackers
directions: Stand each pack of crackers up in rows in
a 9 x 13 airtight rectangle container that is at least 2 inches deep.
The crackers should be tight so that they don't move around.
Whatever crackers won't fit in the rows, use on the sides to fill in the gaps so that all crackers are standing up nice and tight.

title: amish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Stir in apples and vanilla. Bake in large greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add eggs and applesauce; blend. Add sifted dry ingredients; pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350°, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve warm or cold, with ice cream or prepared whipped topping.

title: olympics chicken
directions: Brown chicken in moderately hot oil.
Add garlic and pepper; cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain off excess fat.
In a small bowl, mix together the vinegar, soy sauce, honey and ginger; add to the chicken.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and fully cooked.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chill Jell-O, then whip.
Add rest of ingredients (mayonnaise last) and mix well.
Chill in mold until set.

title: pecan cream cheese squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Stir in pecans; mix well.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs until smooth. Pour over pecan mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water per package directions.
Add frozen, slightly thawed strawberries.
Chill until thickened.
Mix and crush margarine, pretzels, nuts and sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Pour jello mixture over all and chill until served.

title: grilled ham steak
directions: In small pan, combine the preserves, mustard, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over low heat, about 3 minutes.
Put ham steak on the prepared grill.
Grill over medium coals for 10 minutes per side.
Brush with glaze during last few minutes.

title: cucumber ring supreme
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add 2/3 cup water; stir over low heat until dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice. Gradually beat hot gelatin mixture into cream cheese with a rotary beater until smooth.
Have cucumbers and take out seeds.
Finely shred.
Measure 2 cups cucumbers and add remaining ingredients to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into gelatin mold.
Chill until firm. Garnish with cherry tomatoes and watercress.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together. Roll in a ball. Roll ball in finely chopped pecans. Good.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter and chocolate over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar. Mix in eggs and blend well. Stir in flour, vanilla and pecans. Pour into greased 8-inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 12 brownies.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour and 1/2 cup ground walnuts and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; drain and serve.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until done.
Sweeten.
Mix in small bowl the egg yellows, flour and small amount of milk.
Substance should be thin. While rice is boiling, stir in mixture.
Cook until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture; stroke until blended.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.
Let cool 10 minutes. Turn out and finish cooling.

title: saturday night beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole, bean pot or slow cooker.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If using a slow cooker, bake, uncovered, on low for up to 4 hours.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.
Great for potlucks!

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Place apple juice in saucepan and bring to a boil. Combine margarine, cornstarch and spice in small bowl. Add small amount of apple juice and stir until well blended. Stir cornstarch mixture into apple juice. Pour over apples to coat and pour into unbaked crust. Top with top crust and brush with melted butter; sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter-cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar. Beat until
light
and
fluffy.	Add eggs and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture. Cool dough for
hour.
Shape
dough
into
1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart
on	greased cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in water and flatten cookies.
Bake
at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips) with fork until moist.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Stir in chips.
Press into ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish, layer crushed chips, chicken, chicken broth, onion and pepper.
Mix other ingredients (except cheese).
Pour over casserole; top with grated cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla until creamy. Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in oats and gumdrops. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; pour into a 4-quart oven dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Can top with bread crumbs before baking, if desired.

title: easy taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning and mix well. Then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry almond quick bread
directions: Mix dough ingredients well and roll out into rectangle about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll, rolling from wide side. Cut into about 12 rolls.
Place cut side down into orange juice mixture (which has been placed in 13 x 9-inch baking pan).
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Pressure cook cabbage for 8 minutes or cook on the stove and drain.
Brown crumbled ground beef and onion.
Then place all of the above ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours (or overnight; add additional water) or on high for 7 to 8 hours. Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water,
then
add mashed cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in dish or mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt; add beaten eggs and milk.
Stir in melted margarine and vanilla, stir until smooth.
Add coconut and nuts and mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large 9-inch pies.

title: thai chicken barbecue(also great with pork tenderloin)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in an extra large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add chicken.
Seal bag and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Transfer marinade to a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick and easy chicken veggie soup
directions: Skin
chicken
and cut up.
Boil in water until tender. Remove the chicken from the water (broth) and let cool.
After the chicken
has
cooled, remove all of the meat from the bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Add to the broth: onion, carrots
and cabbage.
Cook over medium heat until the carrots and cabbage are
done.
Next
add
corn,
green beans, peas, tomatoes, mushrooms and
macaroni.
Cover;
cook
for 10 minutes.
Add the chicken and cook
another 5 to 10 minutes or until everything is hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed party mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop stems.
In a medium to large bowl, combine chopped stems and all remaining ingredients.
Press mixture firmly into mushroom caps, mounding on top.
Sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 18 to 23 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 35 to 40 appetizers.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 370°. Remove from oven. Layer tomatoes in shell. Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper, basil and garlic powder. Combine mayonnaise and cheese. Spread over tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown. Let pie stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
Cool broth.
Grease mold. Grind or freshly chop all ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and press into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy pan.
Stir until it reaches a boil.
Boil 10 minutes or soft boil stage.
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm and beat until mixture loses gloss.
Requires little beating.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Put in buttered pan.

title: garlic pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops in a little oil in a large skillet with a tight fitting lid.
Remove to a plate.
Add celery, garlic, and onion to skillet.
Stir until slight soft.
Stir rice into skillet and stir to coat with oil.
Pour water over rice and stir.
Lay chops on top.
Sprinkle with extra garlic powder, if desired.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover.
Simmer 20 minutes until rice is cooked. Let stand 5-10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken-n-dressing
directions: Mix flour, meal, 3/4 stick margarine, eggs and enough buttermilk to make cornbread batter.
Bake at 375° until done, but not brown.
Cool.
Crumble into bowl.
Cook onions in remaining margarine.
Add to crumbled bread.
Mix soup, broth, pepper and sage into crumbled bread.
Layer bread mixture with chicken in pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Combine coconut and nuts.
Spread in bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter over coconut-pecan mixture.
Place margarine and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until margarine melts and cream cheese is soft.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Spoon over top of cake (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Do not cut until cool.
Cut and serve individual pieces upside-down.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add
together first seven ingredients.
Stir low temperature until it thickens.
Add green beans and put in baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on beans.
Mix corn flakes and melted butter in separate dish.
Sprinkle on top of beans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together and let it sit 5 minutes.
Take spoonfuls and drop into hot grease and cook until brown.

title: fabulous fruit salad
directions: Scoop cantaloupes, honeydew and watermelon into melon balls. Slice peaches.
Toss melon balls and peaches with strawberries and blueberries.
Chill.
Just before serving, combine ginger ale, honey and orange juice.
Drizzle over fruit.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in pieces.
Cook in boiling water until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Combine all ingredients after squash has been mashed with fork.
Stir and put into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: baked spaghetti ii
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain meat; add spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain cooked spaghetti. Combine spaghetti noodles and spaghetti sauce in oblong pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese over top and bake uncovered until cheese is lightly browned.

title: sanders butter creme frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk until smooth. Cook over low heat until paste is formed. Cool, stirring often. Cream butter and Crisco. Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Add cooled mixture and beat until like whipped cream.

title: clam dip
directions: Rinse the cottage cheese in a strainer and press out any excess moisture (important).
Place in a blender with Neufchatel cheese and blend until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill thoroughly before serving (at least 4 hours).
Yields 2 cups.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and nuts. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill overnight.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer 1/2 head lettuce, then onions, peas, pepper and celery.
Mix remaining 1/2 head lettuce, mayonnaise and sugar.
Layer on top of celery. Top with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Seal. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix butter, water and cocoa.
Boil until butter is melted. Remove from heat and add salt, sugar and flour.
Beat after each. Beat in 2 eggs and soda.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in a well-greased and floured pan.
(Sheet pan is best.)

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Mix; pour into 9-inch ungreased pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Makes its own crust.

title: party salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large bowl in the order listed. Spread with mayo.
Add 1 pound of crisply fried bacon that has been crumbled.
Sprinkle on 1 to 2 cups of grated cheese. Sprinkle on 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and let salad sit overnight in refrigerator.
Mix/toss salad just before serving.

title: jelled cider mold
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cider and gelatin.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve.
Pour into 8 (1/4-cup) molds.
Chill until firm and unmold.
Serve with baked ham.

title: pesto appetizer(makes about 40 appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Halve each pita crosswise.
Brush the inside surface of each circle with pesto.
Cut each pesto-covered pita circle into fourths.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Arrange pieces in single layer on 2 baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Switch pans on racks and bake for another 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Serve.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix the nuts, sugar and cinnamon together and set aside. Grease a Bundt cake pan.
Combine the cake mix, pudding, oil and water.
Mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Set timer and beat 6 to 8 minutes at high speed.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually until mixture thickens.
Then add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Follow directions
on roll mix.
Knead dough until well mixed. Rise to double size.
Roll out.
Make paste with brown sugar, cinnamon
and
soft
butter.
Rub paste over rolled out dough. Roll up jelly roll style.
Cut into rolls.
Place into 4 greased pie
pans.
Let
rise
again.
Bake
on
400° until brown.
(Can use any roll recipe.)

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over high heat (boiling water) until slightly thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and butter; cook until thick.
Put in prebaked pie crust; cover with meringue.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix together and pour over 2 (12 ounce) packages of oyster crackers.
Mix and set for 24 hours.
Oil will not make crackers soggy.
A great snack when friends come over.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook together the first 6 ingredients until thickened. Alternate in serving bowl:
sliced bananas, dressing and chopped peanuts.
Layer 3 to 4 times.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill, broil or pan-fry chicken.
Mix all vegetables with meat.
Mix oil and spices.
Combine all together.

title: rita's homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix together to make dough and roll out as thin as possible. Let dry a little.
Roll up into a log and slice.
Unroll each slice and let dry a little more.
These noodles taste great in homemade chicken soup.

title: nut goodies
directions: Microwave the first three ingredients for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Pour 1/2 of mixture into jelly roll pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Then stir in peanuts in other half and cover.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 340° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until crust is brown and center is solid.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in oven-safe dish and bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cranberry orange delight
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: In a bowl, combine saltines and 1/4 cup butter.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in the 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Stir until tender not brown.
Put in a pie shell.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and nutmeg.
Pour over onions. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set. Place pie plate on a cookie sheet before putting in oven.

title: macaroni delight
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Pour hot milk over crumbs and mix in the cheese, pimento, onion, seasoning and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into mixture.
Add macaroni.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt shortening in a saucepan. Add brown sugar. Stir until mixed. Cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each. Add dry ingredients, nuts and chips.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water to cranberries and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sugar; stir and add gelatin.
Remove from stove and partially cool.
Add pineapple (drained) chopped nuts and apple.
Pour into mold or dish to chill.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cut stem carefully off from pumpkin.
Cut a lid from the top of the pumpkin (about 2 to 3 inches from stem).
Clean pumpkin out (no seeds or stringy pulp); rinse inside with water.
Pat a little brown sugar around inside.
Put in your meat loaf mixture.
Wrap completely in tinfoil.
Cook until tender, about 4 hours at 350°. Serve by cutting pumpkin and meat loaf in wedges.
Put a little butter and salt on pumpkin (do not eat skin).
Delicious!

title: casserole chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and place in a casserole large enough to hold chicken comfortably.
Combine the sour cream, mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spread the soup mixture over the chicken.
Cover with chow mein noodles and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Melt the caramels with milk in a small bowl in microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; stir mixture until smooth.
Pour into crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until smooth.
Stir in applesauce, vanilla and cinnamon. Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Spread over caramel layer in crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and apple slices and drizzle with melted caramels, if desired.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Cook milk, cocoa, sugar and oleo for 1 1/2 or 2 minutes, then add vanilla and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed and quickly spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: gay's casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Slice potatoes into a casserole dish. Cook onion with meat as it browns.
Place in layers: meat, potatoes and mushroom soup.
Bake until potatoes are done, about 30 to 35 minutes, at 350°.
To shorten cooking time, the potatoes may be cooked until tender on the stove.
Sprinkle with cheese for the last 5 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add seasonings, sauce and olives.
In casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat, sauce and cheese. Add water.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well with ground beef.
Pour all of mixture into casserole dish and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Cream the shortening; add sugar slowly.
Add beaten egg.
Add flavoring, then flour and baking powder which have been sifted together slowly with milk.
Beat well and bake in layer tins in moderate oven 12 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Whip cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar.
Blend well; add eggs alternately with flour, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mary's cheat cake
directions: Purchase one pound or Louisiana ring cake.
Place on your own cake platter.
With skewer, make about 10 small holes scattered around the cake.
Inject equal amounts of orange curacao into skewer holes.
Blend confectioners sugar with orange juice and nutmeg.
Drizzle across cake and down sides.
Refrigerate.
Slice and enjoy.
No hassle!

title: make-ahead main dish
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
Set aside.
Gradually beat the sour cream into cream cheese.
Stir in garlic.
Set aside.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl cream sugar and butter.
Add egg; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in blueberries. Fill 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full. Sprinkle with streusel mix.

title: cleo's chicken soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Roll out 1 package rolls in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown ground meat; drain.
Add picante sauce and heat through.
Pour over rolls; top with sliced cheese.
Cover with other package of rolls. Bake according to directions on crescent rolls.
Serves 6.

title: almond horns
directions: Make dough of almond paste, sugar, almonds and egg whites. Roll pieces of dough into crescent shapes a little larger than a finger.
Roll into bowl of sliced almonds and bake at 300° on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper (until light pale brown). Take out onto cooling rack.
Dip each end into warm, melted chocolate melted with Crisco.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour 1/2 cup measure into waffle iron.
Bake about 2 minutes.
Top with fruit or syrup. Makes 8 waffles.

title: tropical fruit bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Mash bananas.
Drain pineapple.
On low speed, beat flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, eggs, bananas and butter (softened) until blended.
Increase speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes. Stir in pineapple and 1/2 cup of coconut.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake about 1 hour.
Cool ten minutes.
Take out of pan and cool completely.

title: no fat apple muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix liquid ingredients. Combine both.
Wash apple but do not peel.
Cut into small pieces and remove seeds.
Dice well.
Mix into batter and add almonds, if desired.
Use a nonstick muffin pan or a lightly sprayed pan. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Enjoy!

title: meatballs
directions: Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients except sauce well.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
Cook in heated frypan until browned.
Serve Tangy Tomato Sauce over meatballs.
Makes 6 servings (2 meatballs each).

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with spoon, then knead with hands.
If mixture is too sticky, add more milk and oatmeal in equal amounts until mixture is consistency for modeling. Harden your creation in refrigerator.
Then eat it for dessert!

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Mix with fingers or pastry blender. Roll into balls the size of marbles.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Drain before serving.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and whip with mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Blend together the remaining ingredients and pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 375° till browned about 30 minutes.

title: cheese and olive spread
directions: Mix together in bowl until well blended.
If you like, add some olive juice to make more spreadable.
Serve on celery, crackers, vegetables, baked potatoes, sandwiches, etc.

title: munkaczina(orange salad)
directions: Peel and slice oranges and onions thinly.
Arrange in alternate layers in bowl.
Pour over oil, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Marinate 1 hour at room temperature.
Top with sliced olives.

title: samp(sweet corn-hazelnut pudding)
directions: Bring chicken stock to boil; slowly pour in corn meal, stirring constantly, until mixture is very thick.
Add nuts, sugar, maple syrup, salt and butter.
Stir in well.
Turn to low heat and stir frequently to avoid scorching.
Serve hot or cold. Serves 20.

title: crisp tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Toss gently. Chill.
Spoon into lettuce cups.
Top with mayonnaise and an olive slice.
Servings:

title: lasagna sausage wrap
directions: Fry sausage.
Cook noodles.
Cut sausage in 3-inch pieces. Wrap each piece in a lasagna noodle.
Place in a baking dish.
Add cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter and chocolate. In a separate bowl, blend the eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt. Blend egg mixture with chocolate and butter, Pour into pie shell. Bake 35 minutes. Serve warm, topped with whipped cream
or ice cream.

title: kathy's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the boiling water with the oatmeal; let stand until cool to touch.
Mix together all remaining ingredients, including the cold oats.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with the pie filling and sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat well 4 or 5 minutes.

title: homestyle sloppy joes("better than in the can!")
directions: Chop onion and green pepper and fry the meat until it is brown.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together and fry for about 10 minutes.
"Slop" onto hamburger style buns.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, tarragon, onion and garlic.
Brown the chicken.
Add the vermouth.
Cover and simmer for one hour.
Add mushrooms during the cooking.
After 1 hour, remove chicken.
Bring liquid to a boil to reduce it.
Add sour cream and mix well.
If separation occurs, add 1 or 2 tablespoons water.
Put chicken on a platter and cover with sour cream gravy. Everybody loves this dish!

title: caramel pecan roll
directions: Grease or spray Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Place rolls around pan, overlapping where necessary.
Mix dry pudding mix and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Combine melted margarine and sugar and pour over pudding mix.
Cover and let set out on counter overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes before turning out onto platter.

title: quick baked ziti
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, Ricotta cheese and pepper in blender until smooth.
Cook pasta; drain.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in Ricotta mixture; top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Add seasonings.
Take bread and cut into cubes, then mix together after bread has absorbed all the butter seasoning.
Place in a large 13 x 15-inch pan and bake croutons at
350° for 15 minutes; stir until all is toasty.
Serve over salads, casseroles, etc.
Store in Ziploc bag until needed.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix with coconut and sugar.
Add orange juice; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut and powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple in a bowl. Form into a ball and wrap in plastic. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll in pecans until ball is covered. Refrigerate again until serving time.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain very well.
Layer in one large casserole or two small or in pie plate for pie-look: beans, meat and onion and picante sauce.
At this point, if you are going to freeze any, cover with heavy foil and place cheese in plastic freezing bag.

title: quick and easy strawberry preserves
directions: Mix well and stir until mixture is like syrup.
Boil 6 minutes and remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.
Boil 6 more minutes and remove from heat.
Skim off foam and pour in containers.

title: no-fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until it forms a hard ball in water (285°).
Place Marshmallow Creme in a mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff or until the candy holds a peak.
Fold in nuts and flavoring.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper or buttered plate.

title: chicken & rice casserole
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes; time will depend on size of pan used.
Example:
A 9 x 13-inch pan will not require quite as long to cook.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Brown the hamburger meat in a skillet, drain fat. Add chili seasoning, tomato paste, and tomato sauce in the hamburger meat. Stir well. Pour chili beans and half of the tomato juice in the crock pot. Add the mixture from the skillet. Add remaining tomato juice. Stir well to mix all ingredients. Cook on high for 45 minutes. Serves about 30 people.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter dish.
Place layer of potatoes. Sprinkle with Season-All and garlic salt.
Layer of ham.
Layer of cheese.
Repeat for three layers.
Fill bowl halfway with milk. Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle mixture over top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: crabtree devil's food cake
directions: To sour milk, add 1/4 cup vinegar to 3/4 cup milk.

title: sweet and sour polish sausage
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on high 5 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts or cherries.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to box directions.
While warm, poke holes all over cake.
While cake is still warm, mix and pour over cake the strawberry jello mixed with hot water and strawberry pop.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: deer kielbasa
directions: Sprinkle seasonings over meat.
Toss until well mixed.
Put in casings.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill 2 hours or longer before serving.
Can be frozen for keeping.

title: quick cookies
directions: Combine the first five ingredients and bring to a boil for 15 seconds.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Then add quick oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper and let harden.

title: raisin molasses gems
directions: Beat shortening and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour, spices and salt.
Add to molasses mixture; mix well.
Add raisins.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add melted margarine; mix again.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans.
After combining ingredients together real well, pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Place as many pecan halves on top as desired.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, squash and vanilla. Mix, then add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brethren cheddar bread
directions: Cut margarine into dry ingredients until crumbly.
Stir in cheese and dill.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Divide batter between 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, until browned and loaves sound hollow when thumped. Good served warm or cool.

title: wild rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into serving size pieces (parboil wild rabbit); salt and pepper to taste, roll in flour and brown.
Pour small amount of water in skillet and steam 15 minutes.
Pour sour cream over rabbit; let cook slowly in oven (275°) or on top of stove on low heat until tender.
Makes nice brown gravy.

title: stained glass window cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll dough into thin coils with your hands.
Shape into forms and place onto cookie sheet that has been covered with foil.
Crush each color (separately) of the hard candy until finely chopped.
We usually put the candy in a towel and hit with a hammer.
Place the crushed hard candy into the open spaces in the dough forms.

title: anna's peach pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg; add flour and continue mixing. Place peaches in uncooked pie shell, then pour mixture over peaches.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in quart jar.
Shake
well	and store in refrigerator. Garlic button may be
dropped in and left for a while if you like garlic flavor.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Mix sherbet and ginger ale together in punch bowl.
Serve after mixed thoroughly.
Makes 25 to 30 (4-ounce) servings.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix well and add diced celery, apples and nuts.

title: chocolate candy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Blend salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Sir in chocolate candies.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until almost set.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In a glass dish, soak chicken in soy sauce.
Let stand for 10 minutes, drain chicken. Discard remaining soy sauce.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all together. Use 2 teaspoons per cup in hot water. Very good for a cold winter day.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Mix last seven ingredients, pour on beans. Refrigerated several hours, overnight if possible. Serve cold. Can add 1 can of drained corn. Can substitute sweetened powders in place of sugar.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Mix pineapple,
juice and eggs. Put in buttered oblong dish. Mix brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen banana milk shake
directions: Freeze banana chunks; when frozen, combine in blender with the milk, sweetener and nutmeg.
Blend just until mixture is thick and frosty.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sugar-free blueberry dessert
directions: Mash blueberries.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add blueberries, lemon juice and Sucaryl.
Heat until berries are cooked.
Pour into mold or molds and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole, placing some noodles on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aebelskivers
directions: Separate eggs. With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Set aside.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat egg yolks until slightly thickened.
Gradually add sugar and salt, beating until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add dry ingredients to egg yolk mixture, alternating with buttermilk until thoroughly mixed.
With rubber spatula, gently fold egg whites into batter until well combined.
Cook in aebelskivers pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli acccording to package. Layer in a 12 x 18-inch dish.
Spread chicken evenly on top. Combine soup with milk and mix until smooth, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese and cook for 30 minutes or until cheese begins to brown.

title: devil dogs
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Drop small tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: aunt ruth's spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook spaghetti.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour cream over spaghetti.
Top with half of the cheese slices and set aside.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease a Bundt or tube pan.
Put nuts in bottom of pan.
Place rolls over nuts.
Mix all dry ingredients and pour over rolls. Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Cover with tea towel and let rise overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn immediately onto serving plate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix 2 quarts ice cubes with cukes, onion and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: cream puff
directions: Heat
oven
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir
in
flour
vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball
(about
minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly,
one
at
a time.
Beat until smooth.
With a spoon drop
in
mounds
3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake
to
minutes
until golden brown and dry. Allow to cool slowly away from drafts.
With sharp knife, cut off tops. Scoop
out soft dough inside and discard.
Fill and replace tops. Sift powdered sugar over top or put a chocolate glaze on.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini and drain.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients with Italian dressing.
Mix well and cover. Refrigerate overnight so all the flavors blend.

title: chicken creole
directions: Dice the green peppers and celery.
Simmer the first 11 ingredients for about an hour.
Add the chicken for a half hour. Then for the last 15 minutes, add the mushrooms.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 5 minutes at medium speed in large mixing bowl.
Important that beating time is 5 minutes.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes before turning out on wire rack. If desired, sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: orange roughy with salsa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 7 ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve as salsa.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bell pepper and seasoning; mix well. Form into balls.
Layer in pan; put in oven to cook.
When down, pour off grease.
Add soup.
Use soup cans and add same amount of water.
For double batch, use 3 cans.
Simmer for 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve with potatoes.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar; beat until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition until mixture stands in very stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pans and form into a nest-like shell, building up sides.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Reserve several whole strawberries for topping.
Slice remaining strawberries.
Prepare cake mix using package directions. Slice cake into thirds horizontally.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in half the whipped topping gently.
Chill until firm.
Place bottom third of cake on cake plate.
Spread 1/3 of the gelatin mixture over top.
Arrange 1/3 of the sliced strawberries on mixture.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mashed apricots and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm. Combine 1/2 cup each reserved juices and margarine, flour, sugar and egg.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and spread over jello.
Sprinkle with cheese and marshmallows.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well and freeze. Add fruit if desired.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium size bowl, combine blueberries, water and tapioca; set aside.
In another bowl, cream the butter.
Add flour and sugar, blending to form crumbs.
Spoon the blueberry mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, then sprinkle the flour and sugar mixture on top.
Bake until berries are tender and the top browned, 40 or 45 minutes.
Serve immediately with or without cream on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, syrup and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, or until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: pepper steak
directions: First prepare green pepper sauce: Saute green pepper, onions, mushrooms and tomatoes in 1/2 cup butter for 5 minutes.
Add Espagnole Sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper steak slices and dredge in flour.
Saute in remaining 1/4 cup butter for 2 minutes.
Add green pepper sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Add wine and simmer for 3 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: ada's brownies
directions: Melt oleo in pot, beat well with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and cocoa, beat well.
Add chopped nuts. Put in greased and floured pan (size 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch, this is very important).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: bagel spread
directions: Mix well and spread over bagels.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Dice all vegetables in a bowl. Combine noodles, vegetables, dry Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and then pour Italian dressing over top of salad; mix well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Let chill several hours and then mix well again prior to serving.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onions, egg, salt, marjoram and thyme.
Shape
into 24 meatballs.
Brown in oil in Dutch oven.
Remove meatballs as they brown.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Place oil in heavy iron pot.
Saute onion and garlic for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook for 10 minutes more.
Add shrimp and cook for a final 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; drain.
Add green pepper and onion until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Add pepperoni.
Mix all together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In frying pan, mix onion, green pepper, ground beef and mushrooms.
Cook until ground beef is done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 hours uncovered.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Let jello thicken but not set.
Mix in sour cream and cranberries.
Pour into mold or 8 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: dorothy's light applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together flour, and salt, set aside.
Blend baking soda and applesauce (this may foam up suddenly, use a 1-quart pan).
Add applesauce and flour mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread into ring pan or loaf pans.
Decorate with candied fruits and nuts.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and 3/4 cup sugar; add butter, 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Cream together.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.

title: barbecued kielbasi
directions: Place ingredients in a crock-pot for 6 hours on low or 4 hours on high.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot and enjoy.

title: angel rolls
directions: Sift flour.
Cut in shortening; add sugar.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to flour mixture.
Roll like biscuits.
Cut with large cutter and fold over.
Let rise after putting into pan until doubled.
After rising, bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine last 7 ingredients and add to the chicken mix and chill.
Serves 8 people.

title: glazed lemon nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large bowl of mixer and beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs and lemon rind.
Sift or stir in the flour with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to original mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan.
Turn right side up on rack to glaze.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar and pretzels. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Dissolve jello in water. Stir in berries. Chill just until it begins to set. Blend cream cheese, brown sugar and whipped topping. Spread on cooled crust. Pour strawberry jello mixture over cream cheese mixture. Garnish with fresh strawberries and additional Cool Whip.

title: secret frosting recipe(first time released from family)
directions: In a little saucepan, combine milk and cornstarch and stir with wooden spoon until mixture boils.
Set aside immediately after it boils and let it cool.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add milk, cornstarch (slightly warm) and vanilla with electric mixer.
Mix until fluffy or until grainy texture is gone.
Flavor with orange or whatever flavoring is desired.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Blend eggs and water; set aside.
Heat oil in hot wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add green onions; stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add egg mixture; scramble.
Stir in rice.
Add shrimp and soy sauce; cook, stirring, until thoroughly heated.

title: western beans casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain and add the onion, green pepper, celery and margarine.
Combine beans, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350°
until hot.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, fruit cocktail, nuts and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.
(High altitude:
let rise 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°; bake 5 minutes.)

title: candy
directions: *Some black walnuts are good in this candy.

title: kentucky pork chops
directions: Place pork chips in large dish.
Combine 2 tablespoons mustard, 2 tablespoons molasses, 2 tablespoons bourbon, if used, or orange juice, 1/8 teaspoon hot pepper sauce and orange rind.
Mix well. Add yams to the chops.
Pour mustard mixture over.
Cover and marinate at room temperature at least 30 minutes.
Remove meat and yams from marinade, scraping off most of it.
Grill, covered, over preheated coals or 4-inches from broiler, turning once, about 6 minutes on each side for the meat, 8 to 10 minutes each side for the yams, until cooked through.
Pork should be white, but still moist when cut.
Yams should be browned and soft.

title: pudding dessert(shaker pudding)
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Let set 5 minutes, then add whipped topping.
Layer a 9-inch dish with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 mixture on top of crackers.
Make another layer of crackers.
Pour remainder of mixture over them. Top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: hot german-style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and set aside.
Pan-fry bacon.
Remove bacon and add to bacon grease the flour; blend well.
Add chicken broth and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until it boils and thickens.
Add chopped onion.
Turn off heat and add sugar and salt.
Cut potatoes and layer with sauce in between.
Top with parsley.
Can do day before.
Reheat at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Stir-fry chicken for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add broccoli, cover tightly and cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, until broccoli is tender.
Stir in teriyaki sauce, water chestnuts, onions and garlic powder.
Stir cornstarch into water, then add to broccoli mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened.
Sprinkle in peanuts.
Remove from heat.
Serve with additional teriyaki sauce, if desired.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, sugar and almond extract until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat on low until blended.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
Stir together the sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Carefully spread on "pie."
Top with fruit in season or thickened pie filling.

title: banana smoothy
directions: Put frozen bananas, cold water, sweetener and vanilla in blender.
Blend on low speed until large pieces are chopped and then blend on high speed for 1 minute or until smooth.
Yields generous 32 ounce serving.

title: crockpot easy french dip sandwiches
directions: Place beef in 3 1/2 to 6 quart slow cooker.
