Mix dry soup mix and beef broth; pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 10 hours or until beef is tender.
Skim fat from liquid. Remove beef; cut across grain into thin slices.
Cut each baguette horizontally in half.
Fill baguettes with beef; cut in half. Serve with broth for dipping.

title: caramel apple cereal squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cereal, apples and peanuts; mix well.
In small saucepan, over low heat, combine caramels and milk, stirring often until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour caramel mixture over cereal mixture; toss to coat.
Press in greased pan.
Let stand 1 hour or until firm. Cut into bars.

title: marilyn's peppers stuffed with tofu & rice
directions: Cook Rice.
In skillet, heat 2 Tbsp.
Oil.
Stir in Onion, Garlic, Celery, and Carrot; saute until vegetables are tender (5 minutes).
Remove pan from heat and stir in the Pecans, Tofu, Tomato Sauce, Brown Rice, Cheddar Cheese, Soy Sauce, Basil, Oregano, and Pepper.
When mixture is slightly cooled, stir in the Eggs.

title: cucumber sticks
directions: Peel, remove seeds and cut cucumbers into sticks.
Mix together the cold water and lime.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand for 24 hours. Drain and rinse. Cover again with cold water and let stand 3 or 4 hours.
Drain well.
Make syrup.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned.
Drain well.
Set aside.
Pour half of corn meal mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet. Sprinkle evenly with ground beef.
Top with cheese, onions and peppers.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fudge pie
directions: In a double boiler or small saucepan, melt oleo or butter and semi-sweet chocolate.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add butter and chocolate.
Pour into pie plate and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Chill and serve cold.

title: scotchies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: swedish cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Soak in vinegar overnight.
Then drain.

title: chicken skillet spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Replace cover until cheese melts.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix together.
Leave loaf in pan until cool.

title: cheese torte
directions: Mix all together and pat into greased spring-form pan.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Rinse tuna fish; then add in a large pan.
Cook on low until mixed well. Takes 20 minutes to prepare.
May change meat to chicken or turkey.
Serves 8 or more.

title: smoky butter basting sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted butter or margarine and vanilla wafer crumbs together.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix remaining 2 sticks of margarine, eggs and confectioners sugar together.
Mix at high speed of mixer for exactly 15 minutes.
Pour over crust. Slice bananas over top.
Spread pineapple over that.

title: fudge squares
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix sugar, eggs, Bisquick and nuts.
Spread in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 16 squares.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Dip is better if made the day before serving.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Ready to serve in 1 hour.
You can use apple pie filling for a change, if desired.

title: rainbow bean soup
directions: *Your favorite: turkey, beef, ham, chicken.
Bones too, of course.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix with mixer.
Pour in ice cream mixer when mixed together good.
Run ice cream mixer until mixer stops or is very stiff. Enjoy!

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package.
Mix meat with milk and stuffing mix.
Shape into meat balls.
Place into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup. Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Layer 1 can of beans in a casserole dish. Sprinkle on some croutons and cheese.
Then add the second can of beans, next spread soup over top.
Poke holes with fork; then add another layer of cheese.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes or in the microwave for 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, salt and water to a boil. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add butter and let cool for 15 minutes. Mix other ingredients with rice and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Chill 8 to 12 hours.
Cook in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and let stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, add drained cocktail, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and a sprinkle of jello, enough
to color salad.
Mix well. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water, then add all other ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Serves 12.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll into ball, then roll in chopped nuts.
Serve chilled with crackers.

title: jimmy's caesar salad
directions: Cut garlic clove in half and rub into wooden salad bowl. Break egg yolk into bowl.
Add 2 to 3 chopped garlic cloves to yolks.
While stirring, add salt and pepper to taste.
Keep stirring and add twice as much oil as wine vinegar.
Keep stirring and add grated Parmesan cheese to taste.
Let sit.
Add romaine lettuce when ready to serve.
Sprinkle with croutons and more cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Debone and save 1 cup of broth.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth.
In skillet, saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add all other ingredients (including chicken, spaghetti and cup broth) except for Cheddar cheese.
Put in casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Cook at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Rub this into brisket, put in large roast pan, add 2 cans of consume' soup, cover and cook at 250° 30 min. per lb. or until done. Take out of pan (cool). Slice against grain of meat. Use 2 c. of juices and 1 bottle Masterpiece BBQ sauce and pour over meat.

title: bacony chicken
directions: Cut 2 slashes across each chicken half. Press 1/2 strip bacon in each slash. Cream butter, Worcestershire sauce and chives. Brush over chicken. Bake in 375° oven until brown and completely done. Brush with pan drippings during cooking.

title: creole spaghetti
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add puree.
Cook spaghetti.
Add sauce; pour into 2 baking pans.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: southern fried okra
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper. Add okra and toss until well coated.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat enough bacon drippings (about 3 tablespoons) to cover bottom of pan.
Add some okra and cook, turning frequently until crispy and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Repeat, adding more bacon drippings as needed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients except cheese and pretzels together. Turn into a 13 x 9 baking dish (buttered). Spread cheese and crushed pretzels on top. Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes, until bubbly throughout. Yields 15 servings.

title: apple slump
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and water and bring to a boil. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and milk and make small dough balls.
Put on apples and cook for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until crisp-tender.
Drain. Open soup and stir in can until smooth.
(Do not add any liquid to soup.)
In large casserole dish, layer vegetables, 1/2 can of the soup and 1/2 of the cheese, cut in large chunks.
Repeat.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, then 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: fried fudge
directions: Use a large iron skillet over slow heat.
Dissolve or melt 1 cup sugar.
When completely dissolved, add 1/3 of the milk.
Stir until the caramel disappears.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Cook until dissolved.
Add 1/3 more milk.
Boil.
Add last cup of sugar. When boiling good, add last 1/3 of milk.
Cook stirring all the time until a little tried in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from fire.
Cool.
Stir or beat until shine begins to leave.
Add nuts and pour in greased plate.

title: jessie evans smith's 90-minute bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of water.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Mix into a soft, but not sticky, dough.
Cut into 3 pieces; let stand for 15 minutes.
Pound each piece 1 minute (mallet), then form into 3 loaves.
Put into greased pans.
Let stand 35 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together, except sausage.
Pour half of batter into 8 x 10-inch pan.
Spread with browned sausage and then the rest of batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail appetizers
directions: Spread soft cream cheese on dinner size plate until entire surface is evenly covered.
Cover cream cheese with cocktail sauce until the entire surface is now red.
Drain shrimp well.
Add shrimp until the entire surface is covered with shrimp.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Great on grilled or baked chicken or pork chops and as a dipping sauce at mealtime with the chicken.

title: paddy seigler's dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies.
Mix butter and cream cheese in small bowl. Set aside.
In large bowl, mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Put crumbs on top and bottom. Alternate crumbs and filling.

title: pineapple cream
directions: Whip heavy cream to a stiff froth.
Boil milk and sugar.
Soak gelatin in water and place in a warm place.
Add this to the boiled milk.
When slightly cool, add the egg yolks, well beaten. Stir in the fruit and juice of the crushed pineapple and lastly stir in the whipped cream.
Place in sherbet glasses in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 2 quart casserole in this order: rice, corn and its liquid, 1 teaspoon of salt, pepper, 1/2 can of tomato sauce, 1/2 cup of water, onion, raw ground beef, 1/2 teaspoon of salt,
pepper,
tomato sauce and 1/4 cup of water. Cover
meat evenly
with
bacon.
Cover
casserole.
Bake
in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Continue to bake for 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar, water and vanilla to 300°.
Pour onto a well-buttered cookie sheet.
Immediately lay on Hershey bars. When melted, spread chocolate evenly over cooked mixture.
Top with nuts.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: firecracker crab salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently and set aside.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt the margarine (a double boiler works best) and blend in the flour.
Slowly add the milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add the next 4 ingredients; mix well and chill. When it's cool enough to hold its shape, shape it into patties. Dip patties into the egg and then into the bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender but firm. Drain well.
In a casserole, toss macaroni with butter and the 3 cheeses.
Add cream.
Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green tomato preserve pie
directions: Wash
firm
green
tomatoes;
skin
if	desired.
Slice tomatoes 1/4
inch	thick.	To
make
tomatoes
crispier, soak overnight in lime
water.
Boil
lemon
slices gently in water for 10 to
minutes.
Remove lemons, make syrup with liquid and sugar.
Add
tomatoes, ginger and cooked lemon rind.
Boil rapidly until tomatoes are clear and syrup thick;
skim.
Cool quickly and stand
in
syrup to plump.	Place preserves in pie shell and bake in a 400° oven until pastry is firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer 30 to 45 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Use on any meat to grill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and mix.
Add sausage.
Roll into balls and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beets
directions: Place in buttered casserole and bake one hour at 350°.
Will serve eight.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with lettuce.
Layer in order given:
pepper, celery, onion and peas.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar. Frost top of salad with mixture being sure to spread to cover and seal edges.
Grate cheese over top.
Crumble bacon over cheese.
Cover dish and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: orange chiffon jello
directions: Dissolve sugar in water. Add pineapple and boil together for 3 minutes. Dissolve Jell-O in hot mixture.
Chill until thick. Add pecans and fold in whipped cream. Chill until firm.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add the sugar, beating well. Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well. Add flour, baking soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Makes 10 dozen.

title: 7-layer ranch dip
directions: In a 2-quart dish, combine soup mix, sour cream and Tabasco sauce.
Evenly layer remaining ingredients, except tortilla chips, ending with cheese.
Chill, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 7 cups.

title: need sweetened condensed milk?(make your own in a pinch.)
directions: In a 2-cup glass measure, add sugar, water and butter.
Micro on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, until mixture boils, stirring every 30 seconds.
Combine in blender with dry milk.
Process until smooth. Refrigerate until needed.
Makes 1 cup.

title: holiday white fruitcake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
When light and fluffy, beat in egg yolks.
Gradually add 4 cups flour and lemon extract, beating constantly until well mixed; set aside.

title: lemon or orange sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch with a little cold water.
Put in boiling water and boil 5 minutes.
Add juice or extract.

title: teri's vegetable dip
directions: Mix and leave in refrigerator for 24 hours. Then serve with fresh cut vegetables.

title: spitz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add beaten egg.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Use a cookie press.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 minutes.

title: potato cake
directions: Peel potato and shred.
Rinse in cold water and dry thoroughly. Beat egg until frothy and add potatoes, cheese, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Heat butter in a large skillet and drop potato mixture by rounded tablespoons into hot skillet.
Brown on one side.
Turn and brown slowly on the other side until done.
I flatten mine out like hash brown patties.

title: marinated beets (no fat, low calorie)
directions: Combine vinegar, dillweed and sweet-n-low with beet juice. Layer beets & sliced onion in jar and pour beet juice over to cover.
Keep in refrigerator.
Good with everything, including sandwiches.
Doubles easily.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together.
Add broccoli.
Pour into a greased baking dish and top with crumbled cheese and crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cut into cubes.
Combine soups and tomatoes in a small bowl; set aside.
Grease a casserole and line with Doritos.
Layer chicken, then soup mix, then cheese in casserole. Let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with additional orange sections.
Quick, easy, one dish salad!! Serves 6.

title: pockets of reuben
directions: Combine milk and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread.
Mix lightly.
Cut breads in half crosswise.
Open each half to form pocket.
Spoon filling into pockets.
Arrange upright in baking pan or for microwaving, on glass serving tray.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until filling is heated, rotating plate once.

title: chocolate critters
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, morsels, margarine and salt.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper-lined baking sheets.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Store at room temperature or refrigerate.

title: pizza macaroni bake
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage, green pepper and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the macaroni, tomato sauce, half the Parmesan cheese, water, oregano and pepper. Transfer to a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and casserole is heated through.

title: spicy coleslaw
directions: In large bowl combine cabbage, cucumber, tomato, green pepper and green onions; set aside.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Put chillies in bottom of a 7-inch dish, sprinkle with garlic salt, spread cheese over chillies.
Beat the eggs with the two tablespoons of milk and pour over the chillies.
Sprinkle with salt and more Cheddar.
Cook at 80% power for 9 minutes.

title: beef cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with party rye and/or assorted crackers.

title: eggplant casserole dish
directions: Melt 2 Tbsp butter or shortening in skillet.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Saute until slightly browned.
Set aside.
Boil eggplant until tender.
Peel and mash.
Add tomatoes and 3 - 4 crackers and egg.
Mix together.
Add onion mix and stir well. Pour into casserole dish.
Mix 3 - 4 crackers with butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to cream mix.
Alternate bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pans.
Remove from pans.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: cold mint orange tea
directions: Brew tea bags in 2 quarts water.
Crush fresh mint in warm tea.
Add remaining ingredients to make one gallon.
Freeze some in ice cube trays with sprig of mint in each section.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook in 400° oven until brown.
Turn oven to 300°.
Cook until set, about 40 minutes.

title: pyramid taco dip
directions: *I use Old El Paso refried beans with green chilies.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together into soft dough; roll out on floured surface and let dry 20 minutes. Cut into strips. Drop in boiling broth and chicken and cook slowly for about 1 hour.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; mix with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayo and taco mix in a bowl.
Spread bean dip in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream/taco mixture.
Sprinkle onions, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese in layers and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased iron skillet for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: zucchini layered casserole
directions: Layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole 1/2 cup crumbs, zucchini, onion, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano each layer and repeat.
Put 1/2 cup crumbs on top with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs, meat side up, in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt.
Top with lemon slices and chopped onions. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine molasses with chili powder and celery seed.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over spareribs.
Continue baking 2 hours longer or until spareribs are tender and well done.
Baste frequently.
Serves 4.

title: qurme sabzi
directions: Saute onion in olive oil in a large Dutch oven until tender. Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add water.
Let it cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh vegetables as dippers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: shipwreck
directions: Slice potatoes; place half of slices in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add beef, salt, pepper, beans and onion.
Arrange remaining potatoes on top.
Combine tomato soup and water; spoon over top of casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours, or until potatoes are tender.

title: rich, rich, rich chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding and milk according to package directions.
Stir pudding into dry cake mix.
Dump into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salt and pepper pork roast
directions: Mix honey and prepared mustard, brush on roast.
Mix salt and peppercorns and roll roast in mixture until well coated.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer reads 170°.
Yields six to eight servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chicken, and reserving 1/2 can of mushroom soup.
Place in large casserole dish.
Top with chicken; salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Add the remaining 1/2 can of mushroom soup to the top of chicken.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: faye's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Can top with coconut and walnuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.
Cool on rack before cutting.
Enjoy.
Can top with whipped cream or ice cream when cool.
Yum!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse with cold water and set aside.
Chop up vegetables, pepperoni and cheese.
Mix all ingredients, cover with dressing and chill.

title: texas chicken
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in pan.
Put chicken pieces on top.
Brush chicken pieces with 1/4 cup of margarine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Test after 1 hour.
May need to add a little more water.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil in Pam coated pan, zucchini, green pepper and onion.
Don't overcook.
Add corn, salt and garlic powder and bacon.

title: easy fish recipe
directions: In a shallow baking dish or pan, line with foil.
Lay fish in pan in single layer.
Spread each fillet with mayo.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Fish will flake easily and be opaque in color when done.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Sift sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar mix.
Use this meringue to line a well-greased pie pan.
Hollow out the center.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Next, beat egg yolks, lemon juice, peel and salt.
Cook until thick, then cool it.
Combine with half of whipped cream and fill pie meringue. Chill for 24 hours.
When meringue comes from oven, it will fall. Doesn't matter filling will cover it.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Mix
yeast
in
warm
water
and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix
all
dry
ingredients.
Add yeast mixture, oil and buttermilk.
Stir
until
well mixed and place in refrigerator for 15
minutes.
Pinch off as much as needed.
Shape and put into an
oiled
iron skillet and bake for 25 minutes at 450°. Extra keeps in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes; cut thin slice from bottom of each tomato to prevent tipping.
Remove pulp from each tomato, leaving a 1/2-inch wall.
Chop enough pulp to measure 1/3 cup. Mix tomato, green pepper, cheese, croutons and salt.
Fill tomatoes with tomato-cheese mixture.
Place filled tomatoes in ungreased baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until tomatoes are heated through, about 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley sprigs or crumbled bacon if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and salt.
Add water and let mixture soften. Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour.
Add shortening, egg and rest of the flour to make a soft dough.
Put in refrigerator.
Will store easily for 1 week in refrigerator.
Take out when needed.
Knead and roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in pan and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 425°.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Put vegetable mix in bottom of oblong pan.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup of cheese over veggies.
Melt 1/2 stick butter over top.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix, cover and make day before.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use to baste ham frequently during last hour of baking.
Makes glaze for 4 pound ham.

title: barbara's good salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt, just until well blended.
Stir in chocolate syrup until no streaks of white remain.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Cool completely in pan.

title: zucchini-carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 bread pans.
In a large bowl beat eggs with oil, stir in sugars, zucchini, carrots & vanilla. Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt & cinnamon.
Blend into egg & oil mixture and add nuts and raisins.
Bake 1 hour or until tested with a toothpick.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: corned beef with dilled cabbage
directions: Place corned beef brisket in Dutch oven; add water to cover. Simmer, covered tightly, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Remove brisket from liquid.
Place fat side up on rack in broiler pan so meat is 3 to 4-inches from heat.
Combine honey and 1 tablespoon mustard.
Brush half the mixture over top of brisket and broil 3 minutes.
Brush with remaining mixture and continue broiling 2 minutes or until brisket is glazed.

title: happiness
directions: Blend all of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a Heart of Joy and sprinkle with Harmony.
Top with a spread of Understanding
and	sweeten
with Respect.	Bake in an oven of Trust and serve with a Tender Smile.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place
sliced
apples
in
greased casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon and sugar.
Blend margarine, brown sugar, flour and oats. Spread
this topping over the apples.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes
or
until
apples
are tender.
Serve plain, with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hot poppy seed ham and cheese rolls
directions: 1. Freeze rolls in package.
Cut through the center of frozen roll sheet to make 2 halves.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Melt butter in	a saucepan.
Add bread crumbs and milk. Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and put into greased pan.
Bake	in
a
moderate
oven until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: houska(bohemian braided bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Place sugar and butter in bowl of electric mixer.
Pour in scalded milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add egg yolks, grated lemon rind, mace, salt, yeast and half the flour.
Beat 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour, then stir in the fruit and nuts.

title: dynamite
directions: Cook sauce together with a little water, then put celery, peppers and onions in sauce and cook slowly for about 3 hours.
Fry hamburg in balls with margarine, throw in sauce and let cook 1/2 hour more, stirring frequently.
Serve over hamburg or hot dog buns.

title: easy hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans, shaking out excess flour. Set pans aside. Place the cake mix, pineapple and juice, mashed bananas, water, oil, eggs, vanilla, and cinnamon in a large bowl. Blend with an electric mixer on low speed for 3 minutes. Batter should look thick and the fruit well blended. Pour batter into pans. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: guacamole(avocado sauce or dip)
directions: Mix in blender until everything is blended well.
(Use for a dip or as a sauce.)

title: warm cherry puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend milk, eggs, biscuit mix, sugar, extract and margarine in blender for 15 seconds or beat on high speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan or 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Spoon cherry filling over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings. Preparation Time:
7 minutes.
Bake Time:
30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, garlic, oregano, pepper and salt to taste, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers and juice and bay leaves. Cover and marinate, refrigerate overnight.

title: fettucine riviera
directions: Cook fettucine noodles as directed on package; drain.
Saute ham, chicken and mushrooms in butter.
Remove from heat and stir in milk, egg yolks and fettucine mix.
Toss with cooked noodles. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes four 1 cup servings.

title: orange apples
directions: Cut the apples into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Prepare bread cubes with melted 1/2 stick butter and brown sugar.
Sprinkle bread over the apples equally.
Set aside.

title: hot hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients but the muffins.
Split muffins and spread mixture on halves.
Sliced halves into four pieces.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven, until nicely browned.
You can make these in advance and freeze.
Serve warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix all together and put on open face bun with slice of cheese and broil until cheese melts.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Spread on other layer.
Top with Cool Whip and finished nuts.

title: quick apple roll
directions: Grease baking dish; add all ingredients and mix well.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Marinate strips of deer meat for 2 hours. Place deer meat on a cookie sheet or line bottom of oven with foil and hang meat in oven racks. If meat is placed on cookie sheets, meat will need to be turned. Set oven for 150-200°. Place meat in oven and cook for 4 hours leaving oven door ajar. Turn meat that is placed on cookie sheet 4 times. If hung in the oven, just leave and check every once in a while. Keep in cool dry place after jerky has cooled from oven. Do not refrigerate.

title: shrimp in tomato sauce
directions: Flour shrimp, then quick fry in wok with 1 tablespoon oil for 1 minute.
Add the garlic and pimentos and continue to fry for another minute.
Add brandy and continue to cook for 2 minutes, then add the butter and stir until melted.
Now add the tomato sauce and fry for a few seconds, just until sauce is heated through.

title: almond chicken
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in bag and shake chicken pieces. Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown chicken in 350° oven for 1/2 hour on each side.

title: frosty fruit cooler
directions: In a punch bowl or large container (2 quart), combine the apricot nectar and pineapple or orange juice.

title: orange chicken
directions: Pour orange juice into baking dish and add soup mix.
Stir. Add chicken.
Chicken can marinate all day or just pop into oven. Bake at 350° until chicken is cooked through.

title: chocolate frosting(frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake)
directions: In a saucepan, melt Crisco.
Remove from heat after melting and add cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Put all sugar in a bowl.
Add chocolate mixture to sugar.
Mix at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 tablespoon more milk, if needed, for good spreading consistency.

title: meatballs a la anner
directions: Crush croutons very fine with blender or mallet.
Combine with ground beef and the rest of the ingredients except the spaghetti sauce.
Mix thoroughly with your hands, using larger amount of spices for larger quantities of ground beef.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Stir together flour and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork tines; top each with a pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and pare raw potatoes, then grate them on fine grater. Quickly stir in onion, eggs, flour and seasonings.
Drop from a tablespoon into 1/4-inch hot fat or salad oil in skillet, spreading each cake with the back of a spoon until it is thin.
Saute to a deep, golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper toweling laid in baking pan.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in jelly-roll pan in 375° oven.
Add single layer of potatoes and cut crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake 1/2 hour or until done and tops are crisp.
Goes well with steaks or any meat that does not allow for making gravy.

title: curry glazed chicken
directions: Coat chicken in mix of flour, salt and ginger.
Roll in butter and place in baking pan.
Combine 2 additional tablespoons flour and ginger with rest of ingredients in saucepan and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Then simmer for 15 minutes or so. Meanwhile, bake chicken, uncovered, for 20 minutes, at 400°.
Take out and baste with half the sauce.
Cook chicken another 15 to 20 minutes, take out and pour over the remaining sauce.
Bake again for 20 more minutes.
This is time consuming but worth the effort. Serve with rice.

title: shake-it-and-bake-it-mix
directions: In a heavy, plastic zip-type bag, combine all ingredients and shake the bag to mix well.

title: eagle brand cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Remove from oven (leave in pan).
Punch lots of holes in hot cake with a wooden skewer.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and coconut cream together.
Pour over cake; let cool completely.
Cover with La Creme and sprinkle coconut over top.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: sugar free orange fruited jello
directions: Place oranges and pineapple tidbits in 9x13 glass dish. Make boxes of Jello and let cool.
Add
Cool Whip to Jello mixture. Blend
thoroughly.
Pour Jello over pineapple and oranges. Combine and refrigerate.

title: red cherry roll
directions: Mix sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add cherry juice and cook 1 minute.
Add butter; let stand.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder and salt; cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a soft dough. Turn onto floured board; knead about 20 seconds, then roll into oblong 1/4-inch thick.
Spread cherries on dough; roll like jelly roll and press edges together.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place on a greased pan and pour cherry juice sauce over top.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
You may shorten this recipe by using a biscuit mix.
Other fruit may also be substituted for cherries.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with Cream Cheese Frosting when cool.

title: onion cheese cornbread
directions: Peel and slice onion.
Cook in butter until tender.
In a bowl, combine muffin mix, egg, milk and corn.
Turn this into a greased 8-inch square pan.
When onion is tender, add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup cheese to it.
Spread this mixture over batter. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Melt together sugar and syrup.
Melt peanut butter.
Mix together.
Add Fritos.
Drop tablespoon size portions onto cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Marinate in dressing for 30 to 60 minutes at room temperature.
In saucepan, simmer vegetables, covered, until tender-crisp, about 7 minutes.
Drain steaks and place 1/3 cup of vegetable mixture on each.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion, wrap with 1 slice of bacon each.
Secure with toothpicks.
Grill steaks over coals or broil for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herb-seasoned chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with butter.
Pour orange juice over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for
1 hour. Serve over wild rice with sauce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: quail with aunt min's gravy
directions: Clean and dry quail, then salt and pepper.
Combine pecans and flour in large bowl; mix well.
Make an egg wash and beat the egg into milk.
Dip one quail at a time first into egg wash, then into pecan-flour mixture.

title: ono hot crab dip
directions: Just before serving, pour taco sauce (Ortega or Rosarita) over dip.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef with oyster sauce
directions: Marinate beef in wine and cornstarch. Set aside.
Bring cooking oil to a full boil.
Drop beef all at once.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
When done, drain out excess fat.
Put beef back in pan, add sliced onions, soy sauce and sugar mixture. Stir 2 minutes.
Remove from the fire. Flavor with oyster sauce. Garnish with green peas.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable-beef spaghetti sauce(low-fat)
directions: In large saucepan cook ground beef, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, carrot and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, zucchini, basil, sugar and oregano.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti or fettuccine according to package directions; drain.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve sauce over pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered. (Could be halved for smaller casserole.)

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Combine chocolate and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Remove from heat stir in butter cool until desired consistency.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in large bowl, cut onions and mix with cabbage. Add sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard together. Bring to boil, pour over cabbage and onions while hot.
Mix well. Put in refrigerator.
Keep for weeks.

title: animal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together.
Beat the eggs until fluffy and add, then add sour cream and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well with other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Keep cool while working with.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked dough crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough milk until it will roll out to desired thickness.
Brush with milk or Wesson oil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut into squares.
Prick with fork.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add condensed milk.
Add lime juice and equivalent of 1 beaten egg (fold in).
Put in pie crust (or graham crust) already prebaked.
Add the rest of the egg whites on top. Bake in 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease 13-inch pan.
Add in order without stirring.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Soak peeled and quartered potatoes in cold water.
Drain water from potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, pepper, parsley and paprika in plastic bag or lunch bag.
Shake potatoes in bag to coat.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan with melted oleo.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°; turn with spatula and continue baking for a 30 minute period.
Add paprika again after turning.

title: pound cake
directions: Let butter soften at room temperature.
Mix with sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Then alternately add flour and cream to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Check after 50 minutes, as all ovens differ.
Invert on wax paper or wire rack and let cool.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt pan or sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone
and
place in casserole dish.
Add soups and mix.
Top
with crackers and dot with butter. Bake until bubbly at 350°.
Serves 7.

title: chicken taco pie
directions: Boil pieces of chicken until tender; reserve 1 cup of broth. Remove bones; cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, enchilada sauce, mushroom soup, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Line a greased baking dish with part of corn chips.
Add chicken mixture and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with remaining chips.
Add reserved chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine with peanut butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
When creamy, beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture one half at a time, beating well after each addition.
Put remaining 1/2 cup sugar in bowl. Roll dough in balls size of a walnut and roll in the sugar.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and lightly press a chocolate kiss on top of cookie. Return to oven and bake 2 to 4 minutes more.

title: liechtenstein sauerkraut
directions: Take 2 strips of bacon, snip and fry crisp.
Drain off most of fat.
Leave enough in pan to saute onion until transparent.
Rinse and squeeze moisture out of sauerkraut.
Add diced, unpeeled apples and brown sugar.
Put lid on and simmer for an hour or more.
This is great served with braised pork ribs or pork chops.

title: rice casserole italiano
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water about 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Cook meat, onions, garlic and seasonings in a large skillet until onions are transparent.
Stir in rice and tomato sauce. Blend cottage cheese and egg.
Arrange half of zucchini slices in a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon on meat mixture.
Spread cottage cheese over meat mixture.
Top with remaining zucchini and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9-inch pie pan with nonstick spray.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
Makes 8 servings, 114 calories per serving.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until smooth, thick and foamy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and well drained pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, spices, nuts and raisins.
Stir gently until zucchini mixture is well blended.
Divide batter into two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans, greased and dusted with flour or lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: meat-vegetable skillet
directions: Brown hamburger in 10-inch skillet.
Drain fat; add nutmeg. Add vegetables and water.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cover.
Turn to low heat and cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: On a round pizza pan, pat rolls to fit pan, fluting edges. Layer sausage, cheese and hash browns.
Blend eggs and milk and drizzle over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in wedges or slices to serve.

title: meatball stew
directions: Beat egg slightly in large bowl.
Add crumbs, onion, garlic, 3/4 tsp. Italian seasoning, salt and 1/8 tsp.
pepper.
Mix in meat.
Shape into 24 one inch meatballs.

title: fudgy almond bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat 3/4 cup margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add flour and mix well. Press on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: yummy pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Then add remaining ingredients.
Serve with gingersnaps!
(Graham crackers or vanilla wafers may also be good choices.)
Be creative!

title: hot mushroom canapes
directions: Wash mushrooms; dry on paper towel.
Chop fine; saute with onion in butter until tender and most of liquid has evaporated. Remove from heat; stir in flour and gradually stir in milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Let cool.
Cut bread into rounds.
Spread with mixture using about 1 tablespoon per round.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Freeze until firm.
Put on foil tray freezer wrap and seal.
To serve, put on cookie sheet; broil about 8 inches from broiler for 5 minutes or until brown.
Garnish with olive slice.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Mix with fork, flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat in another bowl egg, milk and butter or margarine.
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened, then pour into pan.
Spread batter evenly and bake 25 minutes, until golden.

title: fruit cocktail fluff
directions: Pour Jell-O powder over fruit cocktail. Mix well. Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill before serving for an hour or two. Put in large bowl.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 tablespoons ice water and add 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool in refrigerator. Add salt, sugar, pineapple, nuts and juice. Congeal slightly.
Whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip and add to jello mixture.
Pour over bite size pieces of cake in two layers and cover with coconut.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumble together the flour, salt and shortening.
This mixture can be kept in the refrigerator a long time
for future use.
To continue, beat together the egg, vinegar and water, and add to the flour mixture, adding more water if needed to handle well.
Refrigerate for at least 15 minutes before rolling out. This makes 4 pie crusts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit and vanilla pudding at least 2 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, add and mix the Cool Whip into fruit and serve.
Is good dipped over servings of yellow or white cake.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O and hot water in medium bowl.
Then add cold water, lemonade, orange juice, cranberry juice and brandy.

title: cocoa-nut layer cake
directions: In a small bowl, mix cocoa with boiling water.
Cool completely.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) pans; set aside.

title: filling for cream puffs
directions: Whip the cream just until it starts to thicken, then add pudding, milk and vanilla.
Whip all together until thick.
Fill puff shells.

title: creamed beef sauce with noodles
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs.
Meanwhile in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef, onions and dill until meat is browned.
Stir in undiluted soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until heated through.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken asparagus roll-ups
directions: Season pounded chicken breasts lightly with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Place 2 to 3 asparagus spears on each chicken breast half.
Roll up tightly; secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Set aside.
Combine flour, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon thyme and paprika.
Roll chicken in this mixture. Place onions and tomatoes on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, reserving 8 slices of each for top.
Place chicken breasts over vegetables; top with reserved onion and tomato slices.
Combine broth with remaining salt and thyme; pour around chicken.
Cover pan loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting every 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients; blend in flour.
Spread dough onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form cake or torte pan (ungreased).

title: oatmeal caramel pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the margarine or butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats, caramel pieces and pecans; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, milk and butter for 1 minute and remove from stove.
Add peanut butter, uncooked oatmeal and vanilla. Beat until greasy.
Pour in greased pan and cut when cool.

title: jim squares
directions: Mix first five ingredients with mixer until smooth and creamy. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage into 2-quart baking dish.
Fry hamburger and onion. Drain off all grease.
Add salt, pepper, rice, soup and water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour on top of cabbage.
Do not mix it. Bake at 325° for 2 hours, covered.
You can grate cheese on top before baking, if desired.

title: company chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, apple and toasted almonds in a large bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over mixture.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill well before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add salt, butter and soda and stir just to mix.
Add nuts and turn into shallow greased pan. Let stand for a minute or so and then pull quite thin.
When cold, break up.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: garlic spread
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature: add some milk or cream to soften and make smooth.
Add a little seasoned salt and pepper to taste and some parsley. Mince garlic and add as much as you like.
Mix well, top with a bit more parsley or paprika for garnish, refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with your choice of crackers or bread.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Pick chicken in pieces. Crush 1/2 bag of Doritos and place in bottom of 9 x 13 dish. In separate bowl, mix soups and chili powder together then
stir in Ro-Tel. Pour over Doritos. Layer chicken over soup mixtures. Crush rest of bag of chips and sprinkle on top of mixture. Sprinkle cheese all over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Press half of crumbs in a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Add 4 cups diced rhubarb.
Combine second mixture and cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May top with whipped cream.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into 1-inch balls.
Heat soup and consomme until hot and blended.
Add meatballs and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail wieners and bacon
directions: Wrap each wiener in bacon.
Use toothpick to hold in place. Put in crock-pot and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: easy overnight wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.

Put rice in a 3-quart or larger casserole.	Add boiling water and salt and pepper. Cover. Place casserole in oven. Shut off oven and forget it until morning. Refrigerate and heat before serving. Can also be frozen.

title: quick mac florentine dinner
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus mousse
directions: Whip asparagus juice in cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and well-mashed asparagus.
Set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool.
When cool, combine ingredients and add extract and sliced almonds.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares to serve. Excellent with chicken dishes.
Serves 20.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat in saucepan over low heat. Serve in fondue pot or on warming plate with large corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: french nut coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Stir dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream. Pour half of batter into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan lined with greased foil.
Spoon half of nut filling over batter.
Add remaining batter and top with rest of nut filling.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tester comes out clean.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: glazed ham
directions: Score ham in about 1-inch squares.
Place in roasting bag and put in roasting pan.
Melt glaze in microwave slowly.
Pour over ham.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: tomato lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil.
Add onion; cook, stirring frequently until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes; set aside.

title: chicken (turkey) crunch casserole
directions: In large bowl mix everything but topping.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix this
and pour in a 2 quart dish.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients quickly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mint caponata
directions: Dice garlic.
Rough chop all veggies.
Mince fresh herbs, except mint.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together. Next add following 4 ingredients to the first ingredients. Next fold in apples and walnuts. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: In a heavy 4-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugars and milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil; stir occasionally. Cook for 15 minutes after boiling begins, stirring constantly.

title: banana chip muffins
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips. Mix well; make a well in center.
Beat the egg; mix in the oil, milk and mashed bananas.
Stir only to moisten; batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Break
bread
into
fine pieces.
Mix bread pieces with tomatoes and
stir.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in oven at 400 ° for one hour or until thick.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan, 9 x 9. If you double recipe, pour into a greased 9 x 13 dish.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Ovens may vary; should be golden brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours.

title: ham and egg ring(nice dish for a brunch)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, toss ham with parsley and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; set aside.
Grease 6-cup ring mold with cooking spray.
Break 6 eggs into mold.
Spoon ham mixture over eggs; break remaining eggs over ham.
With cooking spray, crease piece of aluminum foil; arrange over mold.
Place mold in roasting pan. Pour hot water in pan to come halfway up side of mold.
Bake egg ring 45 minutes until set.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour Crispix into melted mixture.
Mix just until Crispix is covered with
mixture.
Put powdered sugar in big brown bag (grocery sack).
Add Crispix mixture.
Fold bag down and shake until mixture is coated with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 1/2-quarts. "Crispix" is a must for this recipe.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: Cut corn off cob and scrape cob.
Add salt, pepper and sugar. Add water.
Pour corn mixture into a hot skillet that contains the bacon drippings.
As corn cooks, add butter.
Cook on medium heat until corn thickens.
Reduce heat and let cook for about 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned very moist sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Form into balls.
Flatten with fork to make an imprint.
Sprinkle with sugar or decorate with pecans, cherries or icing in your favorite flavor or design.

title: faye whitmore's shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill well.
(Faye likes more ketchup, more red pepper and less celery and so do I.)

title: beef burgers from the 1920's
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add onions and brick of chili.
Cook until melted and mixed.
Add salt and pepper and cook thoroughly. Add catsup and cook until hot.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture; shake off excess flour.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook garlic, mushrooms and parsley in oil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chicken to skillet.
Cook uncovered about 8 minutes, turning once until chicken is brown. Add wine/chicken broth.
Cook uncovered 8 to 10 minutes, turning once until chicken is no longer pink in center.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Thinly slice or dice the onion.
Drain water chestnuts.
Combine broccoli, raisins, onion and water chestnuts.
Stir together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Mix together with combined vegetables 1 hour before serving.
Fry, drain and crumble bacon into pieces; add when ready to serve.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan and heat almost to a boil.
Lower heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Use for chicken spareribs or chops.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Add V-8 juice, tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti mix.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Let sauce simmer, then layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and cheeses.
Repeat, ending with hamburger sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Mix egg, water, salt, sesame seed and flour.
Dip chicken, which has been skinned, boned and cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces, into batter; drain.
Put oil into heavy pan or deep fryer.
Heat to 375° and carefully add chicken, 1 layer at a time.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until golden.
Drain.
Serves 6.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: In large saucepan, cook macaroni as directed on package, adding potatoes and green beans during last 5 to 7 minutes of cooking time.
Cook until vegetables and macaroni are tender; drain.
In large bowl, combine vegetables and macaroni with olive oil; toss lightly.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 1/2 hours. Add tuna and green onions to macaroni mixture.
Add salad dressing; stir gently to coat.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Saute the onion lightly (not dark) in bacon drippings, about two tablespoons.
Add the sauerkraut, water, caraway seed and sugar.
Cook slowly, about 1 hour, until tender.
Add more sugar to taste.

title: orange muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice and 1/4 cup oil in 1-cup measuring glass.
Beat unsalted butter and sugar in mixer.
Beat egg yolks, warmed to room temperature, one at a time until light and fluffy.
Beat in orange marmalade and orange peel.
Add juice mixture alternately with dry ingredients until just blended.
In clean mixer bowl, beat 4 egg whites at room temperature until stiff, then gently fold into batter.
Spoon into prepared muffin pan and bake 20 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: green stuff(dessert)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in a large bowl.
Melt ice cream in Jell-O water.
Put layer (about 2/3) of cookie crumbs in pan. Carefully spoon Jell-O-ice cream mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate 8 hours or more.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine cream of mushroom soup, milk and black pepper.
Stir in French fried onions and green beans.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 more minutes until golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Pick off bones and set aside.

Saute pepper, onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine. Cook spaghetti, drain and stir in Velveeta cheese while hot. Stir until melted. Add sauteed onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms to spaghetti and cheese mix.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 15 to 25 minutes until hot enough.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and stir all ingredients and put in greased pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: mrs. gertie's cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream again. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Combine salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: herb bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
Place sugar, salt and shortening in large mixing bowl and add milk.
When mixture cools, add flour to make a thick batter.
Mix well.
Add softened yeast and eggs.
Crumble basil, thyme and oregano (not necessary if spices are in spice cans).
Add to batter with nutmeg.
Beat well. Add enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
When light, punch down.
Divide dough into two equal portions.
Shape each into a smooth ball.
Let rest 10 minutes. Shape into loaves.
Place into greased bread pans.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: whole wheat sweet potato muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together at medium speed. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Serve hot with butter.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil;
add
cream cheese.
Take off the stove. Beat.
Add gelatin.
Let
cool 10 minutes. Add onions, celery and mayonnaise.
Put in refrigerator until it begins to thicken (watch carefully).
(It
will
thicken in less than 30 minutes.) Put 1/2 of shrimp
into
the bottom of greased mold. Put other 1/2 into shrimp
mixture and put into mold.	Refrigerate.

title: apple nut pie
directions: Combine apples with sugar, honey, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and juice.
Spread nuts over pastry shell.
Add apple mixture.
Cover with topping.
Bake.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt and set aside.
Cream butter, oil and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy, using electric beater at medium speed.
Beat eggs in one at a time. Blend in vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: melt-away mints
directions: Heat water in the bottom portion of a double boiler at a very low temperature. Place white chocolate in top of boiler with oil. Allow to melt very slowly. In another small saucepan, heat milk just to boil point; add to melted white chocolate. Add vanilla, about 4 drops of red food coloring and extract. Using a plastic spatula, pour onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet and spread thin (1/4 inch to less than 1/2 inch thick). Let cool several hours. Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: pat's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in large casserole dish.

title: irma's strawberry pie
directions: Add together the sugar, cornstarch and salt. Cook until thick. Spread the cream cheese softened with milk over the pie shell. Place some sliced strawberries on top of cheese. Put thickened strawberries on top. Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Garnish top with sliced strawberries.

title: steamed mussels
directions: In a large pot, saute shallots and garlic and then add all other ingredients.
Cover pot and steam over medium heat until shells open (about 5 minutes).
Serve in bowls with broth poured over and lots of crusty bread.

title: taco dip
directions: With electric mixer, mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Blend in (by hand) salsa.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Shred lettuce and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While warm, punch holes in top with spoon handle.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with cream of coconut. Saturate cake.
When cool, spread Cool Whip, then cover with coconut.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cherries. Place in tube pan; put cherries on top. Bake one hour or longer at 200 degrees.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit pieces in a bowl. Gently toss with yogurt to coat. Cover and chill several hours. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: texas hot dog surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except buns) in large bowl.
Spoon into buns; wrap in foil.
Heat in oven for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all together and put in bowl.
Sprinkle coconut on top and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Add cherries and mandarin oranges on top for color.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, molasses, egg and cold water. Dissolve baking soda in the hot water and stir in.
Combine flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt together; add to molasses mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and melt butter.
Add together with flour, sugar and seasoning.
Add corn and milk fast.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sue moore's cake
directions: Mix together and bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine garlic and salt; rub with garlic mixture on grill rack.
Place chicken, skin side down, directly above medium coals.
Grill, uncovered, 1 hour or until tender; brush with barbecue sauce and serve.

title: quick soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Using a liquid measuring cup, dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Combine flour, salt and sugar in large bowl and mix well.
Add the yeast and water mixture and mix well.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onion and pepper until done; drain fat. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into crock-pot on high until well heated, then turn to low and cook 4 to 5 hours.

title: favorite pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pineapple and juice.
Mix well and pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2
hours at 325°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease pan with butter (bottom and sides).
Mix cake mix; add one egg and butter; mix with mixer.
Then form a soft dough.
Press into pan evenly.
Take pecans and sprinkle over top.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 3 eggs in a bowl.
Pour over the top of the cake.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When it browns and comes away from pan, it's done.
Cut into squares.

title: flour paste
directions: Mix flour and water and stir until creamy.
Add 1/2 teaspoon powdered resin to mixture and a few drops of peppermint or wintergreen oil (which helps to preserve it).
Makes 1/2 pint.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease small casserole dish.
Stir all ingredients together in dish.
Slice butter or margarine 3 or 4 places on top of corn. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; slice butter in and add dates.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Put vanilla in and stir and add to Krispies and pecans.
Mix in balls and roll in coconut.

title: german sour cream potatoes
directions: Chop warm potatoes into bowl.
Add eggs and onions.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble over potatoes.
Retain grease and add rest of ingredients to bacon drippings.
Bring to boil, stirring to combine ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Serve warm or cold. Serves 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: quick rum cake
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom of greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix other ingredients, pour over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lady lock filling
directions: Cream all ingredients together and add 1 lb. of powdered sugar gradually.
Beat until creamy.
Fill shells.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Heat oil in a large skillet. Add chicken and cook over moderate heat until meat turns white (approximately 5 minutes).
Add pepper, onion, celery, chestnuts, water, salt and ginger.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce together.
Stir into chicken.
Add bean sprouts and cook about 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir often. Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, combined.
Drop into heavy, greased Bundt pan.
When all pieces have been coated, sprinkle remaining mixture over biscuits.
Melt and combine the margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add the nuts.
Pour over tops of biscuits. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread cottage cheese in a greased 9 inch pie plate.
Cook the ground beef and drain.
Stir in 1/2 c. mozzarella cheese, salt, oregano and tomato paste.
Spoon over cottage cheese.
Stir together milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 30-35 minutes or until center tests done. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 1-2 minutes or until melted.
Serves 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9-inch round pans.
Slice each to make 4 layers. Make pudding as per instructions.
Crush frozen Heath bars with hammer.
In a punch bowl or large round casserole or bowl, layer alternately the cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Make 4 layers of each.
Refrigerate.
Serve with large spoon.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add milk and flour.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat good after each egg is added. Add flavoring.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: grandmother's corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into heated, oiled cast-iron skillet. Place in preheated 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Top with crushed crackers, which have been combined with melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs, chocolate and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
If mixture seams thin, chill and then beat again.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spoon into graham cracker crust and chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: biscuit cakegroves, texas
directions: Cut biscuits in halves, then in fourths.
Place in lightly greased and floured bunt pan.

title: macaroni-sauerkraut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, then put in greased loaf pan.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kartoffelroesti(fried potatoes)
directions: Kartoffelroesti is one of the national dishes of Switzerland.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
In a large pan, mix together soups and clams.
Add half and half.
Add clam juice.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 200° for 4 hours.

title: lasagna by melba
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in large saucepan until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with a fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, parsley, sugar, salt, basil and oregano.
Reduce heat; simmer while cooking noodles.

title: can apple pie filling
directions: Cook mixture until bubbly.
Take from stove and add 3 teaspoons lemon juice and you can add yellow food coloring if you want to for color.

title: oatmeal cookies(from a cake mix)
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, oats and sugar. In a small bowl, beat together eggs and oil; add to dry ingredients. Stir in pecans and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart. Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: martha's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add eggs and Eagle Brand, vanilla and Cool Whip; mix gently with spoon.
Add to ice cream freezer container, add fruit if desired.
Fill to line with milk.
Follow remainder of directions as per ice cream freezer instructions.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, dry and slice into 1/3-inch slices.
Stir egg and buttermilk together.
Mix flour and cornmeal.
Heat shortening or oil in a large skillet on medium high.
Dip tomato slices in egg mixture then in flour mixture.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Simmer raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Sift sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon together.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in raisins and salt.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add cream of tartar; beat until thick.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar very slowly; beat until stiff.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: parslied carrots
directions: Cut carrots diagonally; steam 8 minutes. Add rice syrup and garlic powder; let sit.
Chop parsley; add to cool carrots.
Serve at once.

title: grandma's beef stew
directions: Heat tomatoes, water, onion and celery to boiling.
Then add the meat.
Cook 5 minutes; lower heat and add salt and pepper. Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add water, if necessary.
Add the vegetables the last half hour of cooking time. Add chili powder and thicken juice with flour and water just before serving.
Cooked green beans or peas may be added, if desired.

title: lemonade cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy. Add Crystal-Lite. Beat. Add milk; beat until smooth, then fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: apple muffins
directions: Grate apples coarsely.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar substitute, vanilla and spices.
Crumble bread into egg mixture and mix well.
Blend in grated apple; spoon mixture into 6 nonstick muffin pan molds.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes. Let cool before removing from pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin; stir until well blended.
Cool.
Wash and hull strawberries.
Slice into baked pie shell.
Pour gelatin mixture evenly over. Refrigerate.
Gelatin will not be as thick after it is added, but will thicken in the refrigerator.
Won't be of Jell-O consistency but will be more like a soft custard.
When ready to serve, whip cream and sweeten to taste with sugar.
Spread evenly over entire pie.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off of cans. Cut apples in chunks.
Add all together in large bowl and mix well.
Keep cold until serving time.

title: swiss alpine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Drain broccoli.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese. Sprinkle onion over this.
Mix warm milk in eggs. Add salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shaker corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into greased and buttered casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir once halfway through cooking.
When done, it will be golden brown and a silver knife, inserted in the center, will come out clean.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Cook beans and salt in enough water to cover.
Drain, keeping 1 cup of liquid.
While beans cook, cook celery and mushrooms in oil until celery is crisp and tender.
When beans are cooked, mix hot liquid with starch, bouillon and soy sauce.
Then stir into celery and mushrooms.
Add to beans.
Cook until thickened.
Cover with almonds.

title: won tons
directions: Combine ground beef, shrimp, onion and water chestnuts.
Place small amount on won ton skins.
Fry in oil, then steam with water and soy sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: Layer wafers and bananas in large bowl.
Cook other ingredients until thick on medium heat (stirring constantly).
Add flavoring after removing from heat.
Pour over wafers and bananas.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Prepare bread for dressing.
Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add to the bread crumbs and seasonings.
Stir in beaten eggs and enough broth or milk to make a moist dressing. Pan dressing should be very moist.
Just before pouring mixture in pan, stir in 3 teaspoons baking powder for added fluffiness.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni; add cheese.
Brown ground beef; mix ground beef with macaroni and cheese.
Then add stewed tomatoes and chili powder.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, powdered milk and salt. In separate bowl, mix water, yeast and sugar; let rise about 20 minutes. Add eggs and oleo. Mix all together, adding enough flour to dough to be stiff enough to handle.
