Roll out dough and cut into biscuit size. Put on buttered pan and let rise until doubled in size, about 30 to 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of mix into a 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels and mix in evaporated milk and butter.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining cake mix on top of chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add cheeses to eggs and beat well.
Add 1 pint of sour cream, sugar and salt and beat again.
Mix with noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and cook over low heat until a soft ball is formed when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla and butter.
Cool and beat until creamy, then pour onto a buttered plate and cut in squares.

title: moussakas tis formas(molded moussaka)
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan; blend in flour until smooth. Slowly stir in milk.
Add salt.
Cook sauce, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
With a whisk, beat eggs into sauce.
Add cheese and mix well.
Pour sauce into meat-tomato mixture; mix well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken and shrimp savoy
directions: Drain shrimp and
set
aside.
Combine soup and sherry. Stir in chicken,
shrimp, seasonings, pimentos and peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Fold in
sour	cream.	Serve
over beds of fluffy yellow rice.

title: roasted rosemary chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces, removing any excess fat and the wing tips.
Pat dry.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Place the olive oil in a non-stick skillet over low heat and wilt the onion. Stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add the garlic and cook. Stirring 5 minutes longer.
Add the minced Rosemary leaves. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Toss the chicken with the onion mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with the Marinara sauce.
Pour the water into the bottom of the pan and bake until the chicken is cooked through, about 60 minutes, basting often. Serve the chicken on a small platter and spoon the sauce over the top.
Garnish with the Rosemary sprigs.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix together Jell-O and water.
In another bowl mix softened cream cheese with sugar; add Jell-O mixture.
Beat until blended. Take the Pet milk which has been in the freezer and is chilled and icy;
beat until it is thick and fluffy, like Cool Whip but not stiff.
Add the Jell-O mixture, folding together with a wood spoon.
Do not use a metal spoon, it will flatten the mixture. Spread mixture over cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve.
You can sprinkle a few cracker crumbs over the top for decoration.

title: sliced orange and onion salad
directions: Peel and slice orange into thin circles.
Alternate with thin slices of Bermuda onion.
Serve on spinach leaves.
Sprinkle with Italian dressing.
Quick, easy and good!

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Put crushed Oreos and butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on top and sprinkle with peanuts.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over peanuts and freeze.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a large, heavy skillet or a Dutch oven with tight-fitting cover over moderately high heat (about 325°).
Remove bacon bits and all but 1/3 cup bacon fat.
Add raw rice and cook over moderate heat (about 250°), stirring constantly, until rice is golden brown.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Add the cooked bacon and remaining ingredients except almonds.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low (about 200°) and cover tightly.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: molasses candy crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream the butter with salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Blend in molasses and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut or nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on sheets and remove.

title: quick orange marmalade
directions: Bring oranges and lemons to a boil in 2 quarts water; boil for 3 minutes.
Cool in cold water.
Cut oranges and lemons in 8 sections each.
Scoop out pulp, discarding any seeds.
Cut up and place in large kettle.
Slice rind paper thin and add to kettle. Add the additional lemon juice and water.
Heat to boiling and simmer for 1 hour, uncovered.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved. Return to heat and heat to boiling and simmer for 50 minutes. Remove from heat, test for doneness by dipping a teaspoon of the hot liquid onto a chilled plate.
Place in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
If jellied at the end of the time, the marmalade is done. If not, continue cooking a few more minutes.
Test again.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and cover with melted paraffin wax. Yield:
4 pints.

title: white pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix together sugar, water and flour in large bowl.
Continue to mix adding eggs, vinegar, margarine and pecans.
Pour into pie shells and cook for 1 hour.
Cool completely.
Makes 2 pies.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Cover with water for gravy.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks.

title: taco chicken wings
directions: Combine flour and taco seasoning mix.
Roll chicken wings in flour mixture.
Roll into melted butter, then corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna stroganoff
directions: In a large nonstick skillet cook onions and mushrooms over low heat just until tender.
First cover skillet to create steam, then uncover and lightly brown vegetables.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, catsup and pepper.
Dissolve cornstarch in water in a measuring cup.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Add yogurt and tuna. Adjust seasoning if desired.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Divide evenly into 2 portions.
Serve each portion over 1/2 cup rice. Makes 2 servings for evening meal.

title: valerie's spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Using unsliced pumpernickel loaf, scoop out center of loaf and butter inside of bread bowl.
Put dip in bread bowl and serve with cubes of remaining loaf.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs and salt.
Cream altogether. Add applesauce, pineapple and soda in warm water.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix raisins, nuts and spices in flour.
Add to liquid mixture and combine.
Put in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in 350° oven.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt, and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Beat milk and egg together, add to flour mixture.
Knead on floured board, roll out dough, cut biscuits and freeze.
When ready to use:
place frozen biscuits on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy hamburger dish
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; pour off the grease.
Add the Ragu sauce to the ground beef, simmering for about 20 minutes. Cook the noodles done and get a baking dish.
Spread the hamburger meat in pan.
Cover with the noodles and sprinkle with the cheese all over the hamburger and noodles.
Cook for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix well and press in bottom of pan, reserving 1 cup of mixture.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls on cookie sheet; do not stretch.
Pinch edges together to form a crust.
Bake according to package directions; cool.
Mix mayo, cream cheese and Ranch dressing together.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of baked rolls. Press veggies lightly into cheese.
Chill.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: sugar-free bread or rice pudding(microwave)
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Place in non-metallic heat resistant casserole.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until center becomes firm.

title: coca cola salad
directions: Drain juice to make 1 cup and heat.
Pour over cherry and strawberry Jell-O.
Mix well and then add Coca-Cola.
Chill slightly and add nuts and cream cheese (chopped up).
Use 1 large Pyrex dish.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef;
drain off grease.
Melt cheese; add ground beef and
enough tomatoes and juice to dip consistency. Keep hot in chafing dish.
Serve with Fritos.

title: sun-dried tomato bruschetta
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving oil.
Julienne tomatoes.
Mince 3 cloves of garlic and saute with onion in 2 tablespoons reserved oil until soft.
Stir in tomatoes and continue cooking until mixture is uniform in color, about 2 minutes.
Add sugar and season with salt to taste.
Remove from heat and stir in capers.

title: seafood salad(baked)
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery.
Combine with seafood, Worcestershire sauce, seasoning, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter (in a full size shallow baking dish).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with lemon.
Serves 4. Serve chilled over lettuce and lemon.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish and bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, nuts, coconut, vanilla and flour.
Beat gently after each addition only for a few seconds.
Mix in cornflakes, gently folding by hand.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Drop by small tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely.
Combine stems, cheese, softened margarine and onion.
Place the mixture into the mushroom caps.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until the filling has melted and is slightly golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cut in margarine; set aside. Combine 3/4 cup of sugar, cherries and water; cook and stir
until slightly thickened and bubbly; stir in 1 tablespoon of margarine. Reduce heat and keep hot.
Combine egg and milk; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Use fork to mix until moistened.
Transfer hot cherry filling to an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round dish.
Immediately spoon biscuit mixture on top in 4 mounds.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine with sugar.
Add water, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix in oats.
Chill until firm.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in freezer.

title: crabby burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, in a bowl.
Toss mixture lightly, but well to blend thoroughly.
Heat corn oil in a large heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
(A piece of bread dropped into the oil will turn golden brown when the temperature of the oil is just right.)
Form crabmeat in 12 patties, approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Fry crab patties until golden brown, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove crab patties from skillet with tongs and dry on absorbent paper.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.
tags: generous sprinkling freshly ground black pepper

title: coconut custard pie(no crust needed)
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan or deep dish pie plate.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: polka-datas
directions: Combine the dates and hot water; cool and set aside.
Cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, baking soda and salt and add gradually.
Stir in date mix to flour mix. Add the vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread batter in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with chopped nuts or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook celery in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Do not drain. Add butter, water chestnuts, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly. Put a layer of 1/3 of the Chinese noodles in casserole.
Top with 1/2 celery mixture, then more noodles and rest of celery mixture. Cover with last of noodles.
Bake, covered, 10 minutes, then uncovered for 5 minutes more.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat oven to 400° and drop by teaspoonfuls.

title: dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; salt.
Blend the white sauce with milk, dill weed, curry powder and Beau Monde.
Add mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken sprinkled with Lawry's seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: date puff
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Sift dry ingredients into date mixture.
Add beaten egg and all other ingredients.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 250° in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: easy raisin coffee cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, 6 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder and allspice.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in raisins.
Turn into greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pan.

title: brandy alexander pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, whipped cream, creme de cacao and brandy in a large bowl.
Pour into prepared crust. Refrigerate until firm. Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small pieces.
Mash when done.
Mix in all ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Bake in buttered baking dish in a 325° oven about 30 minutes, uncovered.
You may mix the 3 types of squash.
You may use just Cheddar cheese or add the Swiss.

title: herb dip
directions: In blender container at medium speed, blend cottage cheese until smooth; spoon into small bowl. Stir in parsley, onion, dill and chives. Cover and chill 1 hour or until serving time. Garnish with parsley sprig. Serve with Twigs sesame and cheese snack sticks. Makes about 2 cups.

title: nestle holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in medium pan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined pan (8 x 8-inch).
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: caroline's bulgar salad
directions: Soak bulgar in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Add rest of the ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Whisk dressing, pour over salad and toss; cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or preferably overnight.
May also add tomatoes (chopped).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in casserole.
Sprinkle onion over potatoes; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour Cheddar cheese soup over potatoes and pour milk over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla, egg, soda and flour.
Add oats and mix well.
Stir in raisins and chocolate bits.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet; bake in preheated oven at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: carrot beef loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order given.
Grease a shallow pan. Place mixture in pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: slo rise bread
directions: In a 5-quart bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add cold water, powdered milk, oil, sugar and salt; stir well.
Gradually add about 6 cups flour, stirring well after each addition so no flour pockets will remain at the bottom of the bowl. Dough should feel as if ready to knead.
Cover with plastic wrap; let stand in draft-free place overnight.
Turn dough out on floured surface, adding flour if necessary.
Divide in half and shape to fit 2 greased 9 x 3-inch pans.
Cover with plastic wrap; let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on rack.

title: divinity
directions: Cook to hard boil; then pour over one pint of marshmallow cream.
Beat and pour into pan.
Chill.

title: chicken green enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Mix the enchilada sauce, chicken soup and sour cream. Set aside.
Mix the chicken, ripe olives, onions and 3/4 cup sauce. Put 1 1/2 cups sauce in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with 6 flour tortillas, chicken filling and cheese.
Cover filling with remaining 6 flour tortillas, sauce, grated cheese and remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set for about 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
This is better if you make ahead and let set for several hours before baking.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup in a large mixing bowl. Mix with fork until well blended.
Pack lightly in 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Spread catsup over top.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 420°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cake:
Cream 3/4 cup butter, oil and sugar; beat in eggs. Beat in buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, flour and baking soda.
Add cloves and cinnamon and fold in zucchini.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour and oleo to make a crust.
Press in pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs diagonally into bite size pieces.
Heat mustard and jelly in heavy saucepan; add hot dogs and heat through.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: hamburger in oven
directions: Divide meat into 6 to 8 equal parts and make into patties. Season to taste.
Place on foil in large baking pan and arrange onion slices on top of each patty.
Place fries around them.
Wrap foil tightly and bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Each quiche serves 4 to 6.

title: whipped jello
directions: Let jello set in water until syrupy.
Add sugar and beat well. In a large bowl, beat milk and lemon juice until fluffy. When whipped, combine with jello.
Fold in fruit.
Pour over graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: nana's molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill for few hours until firm or freeze for 30 minutes. Grease pans with 1 teaspoon shortening.
Spoon out mixture. Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Place 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake. Makes 30 cookies.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Prepare box of cake mix according to package.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cake mix evenly.
Bake 1 hour or 1 hour and 5 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mrs. haithcox's yellow pound cake
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and milk. Mix other ingredients; add flour last, a little at a time.
Use greased and floured stem pan.
Bake at 325° for about an hour or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Place on cooling racks.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown meat in large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring to separate meat; drain. Reduce heat to medium-low. Add cream cheese, salt and chili powder; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend and chill.
Good with raw vegetables.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Nuts may be added.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease baking dish.
Crush crackers in mixing bowl and add oysters, milk, salt and pepper.
If thin, add a few more crackers and pour into baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown or about 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Take from heat and add chocolate chips.
Beat until well mixed and spread on brownies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Simmer chicken until almost tender.
Arrange broccoli, chicken and soup mixture in layers, ending with cheese.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package. Cook rice and drain. Add chopped onion, cream of mushroom soup. Mix egg and milk and add to mixture. Add 3 c. cheese. Mix well. Put in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes. Take out and add remaining cheese on top and cook for an additional 15 minutes.

title: tar heel fruit pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar in bowl; mix until smooth.
Beat cream in small mixer bowl until stiff peaks form. Fold into cream cheese mixture gently.
Place banana slices over bottom and around side of pie shell.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over bananas.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Combine blueberries, remaining 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Be careful not to break the berries.
Cool.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Yield:
6 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as on package.
Drain well.
Mix all other ingredients, reserving grated cheese.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This can be used with a crust on top (delicious).

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line mini muffin tin with foil liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, lemon juice, salt and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well. Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/4 cup sugar over 2 cups fresh fruit.
Mix together and set aside.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter; add crumbs and sugar.
Pat in pan.
Prepare Dream Whip as on package.
Set aside.
Cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Put pie filling on top and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, Wesson oil and sugar. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla; mix.
Pour in 5 (8-inch) pans.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 Tbsp sugar in lukewarm milk and water.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mixture wil be thick.
Mix last ingredients real well and pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top will turn golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pickled turnips
directions: Cook items for the sauce until the sugar has melted.
Cool and add to sliced turnips in a jar.

title: ba ba's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown sugar, granulated sugar and eggs. Dissolve soda in hot water and mix alternately with flour sifted with salt.
Lastly add nuts and chocolate that has been cut in pieces the size of a pea. Flavor with vanilla and drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: deep butter cake
directions: Mix beaten egg, melted margarine and cake mix together into crumb mixture.
Pat and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: amish bread pudding
directions: Combine the milk and butter until melted (let cool).
Combine the eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Beat at medium speed.
Pour over bread and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Use oblong pan.)

title: jeannie's potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine with onion, salt and pepper, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Add melted butter last.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in water.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir
in	raisins
and
nuts.
Drop
from teaspoon 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate	oven
for 10 minutes. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: green pea salad
directions: Decorate with sliced egg and pimentos and sprinkle with paprika.

title: snickers bar salad
directions: Cut up apple into bite sizes.
Cut up bananas into bite sizes. Add seedless grapes.
Cut up candy bars into bite size pieces. Mix.
Add Cool Whip and mix.

title: pan haggerty
directions: Heat the butter and oil in a large heavy based frying pan. Remove the pan from the heat and put in layers of potatoes, onions and grated cheese, seasoning well with salt and pepper between each layer and ending with a top layer of cheese. Cover and cook the vegetables gently for about 30 minutes or until the potatoes and onions are almost cooked.
Uncover and brown the top of the dish under a hot grill.
Serve straight from the pan.

title: ice cream at home
directions: Mix together in a small Ziploc baggie.
In a large Ziploc baggie, place a tray of ice cubes and about 1/3 cup of table salt. Place the sealed baggie of milk mixture in the large baggie.
Seal the large baggie.
Shake the contents for about 5 minutes.
The liquid will turn to a solid.

title: chinese egg rolls (shrimp)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg roll wrappers.
Place 1 tablespoon shrimp mixture in center of each wrapper.
Roll up. Fold edges in.
Seal by dipping finger in water and moistening wrapper edges.
Fry in deep, hot fat for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 25 rolls.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
Cream sugar, butter and vanilla thoroughly with mixer for 8 to 10 minutes, until fluffy.
Blend in cooled flour mixture until sugar is not grainy. Makes enough to cover 4 layers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Stand cucumbers and onions in salt water for 1 to 2 hours. Heat vinegar and other ingredients.
Drop in warm vinegar and boil 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake until rice is tender, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat and mix cake mix, eggs and oil or butter. Fold in oranges.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Dissolve the yeast in warm water. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of sugar, stirring again, then let stand until completely dissolved.
Cream shortening with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add the beaten egg and scalded milk (which has cooled).
Add the salt and finally the yeast.
Stir in the flour gradually until the dough is stiff enough to knead.
Knead until smooth and elastic for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg white, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg.
Fill each shell with a heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asian burritos
directions: In a pot, bring enough water to cover noodles to boil. Soak noodles in hot water until tender. Rinse with cold water. Soak rice wrappers in water one at a time on a plate until soft, about 1 minute. Drain off water. Place on the wrapper small amount of rice noodles. Top with your favorite ingredients such as cooked shrimp, cooked and minced pork, sliced cucumbers, carrots, avocados or Mung beans or small romaine lettuce leaves. Take wrapper and roll up like a burrito. Repeat. Make about 2 to 4 per person.

title: bean bundles
directions: Arrange green beans into bundles of 12 beans each. Wrap each bundle with half a slice of bacon. Place in baking dish. Drizzle Catalina dressing liberally over beans. Marinate several hours in refrigerator. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Turn at halfway point.

title: split pea soup with ham(8 cups or 4 servings)
directions: In a large pot, cook split peas, bouillon and onion in 12 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce and simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add carrots and simmer 20 minutes.
Add ham and simmer 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: chocolate morsels
directions: Cream the butter until light.
Beat in the brown sugar.
Mix until creamy.
Add the vanilla and egg yolk.
In a bowl combine the flour, baking soda and cocoa powder.
Add to the butter mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Shape by teaspoonful into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.

title: mound bars
directions: Combine graham crackers and butter and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix milk and coconut and spread on cooled crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt chips in a double boiler.
Spread on top of baked coconut layer.

title: veal cutlets italian
directions: Combine bread crumbs, grated cheese and paprika in a pie plate.
Mix thoroughly. Coat veal cutlets lightly with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over moderately high heat. Add cutlets and brown 4 to 5 minutes on each side until fork-tender.
Serve immediately with tomato sauce.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Serve with spaghetti or macaroni of choice or noodles. Serve green vegetable, broccoli, spinach or zucchini.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift
together	flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Cream together
margarine
and
sugar until light and fluffy. Beat
in egg and vanilla.
Stir in Baby Ruths and dry ingredients until well blended.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Drop dough by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10
to 12 minutes, or until done.	Remove from sheets and cool on wire racks.

title: 5-minute fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in saucepan over low heat; heat to boiling and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir into mixture 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan or bowl.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Makes 2 pounds.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Season each piece of chicken with salt, pepper and paprika. Place in roasting pan or any 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with vegetables; dot with margarine.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
(Veggies taste like pot roast veggies.)

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into small bite-sized pieces.
Add pineapple, Mandarin oranges, celery, pimento, green pepper, onion and cashews.
Mix well.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook on low heat 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and boil for 20 minutes. Pack in	pint jars and seal.
Process 20 minutes boiling water bath. Makes 10 pints.

title: bacon wrapped pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloins in a baking dish.
Combine all ingredients except bacon and green onions; pour over tenderloins.
Marinate at least 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 425°. Remove tenderloins and wrap each one with bacon.
Reserve the marinade.
Return tenderloins to the baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Pour reserved marinade over tenderloins and cook for an additional 10 to 20 minutes or until meat thermometer reads 160°. Place on a serving tray and sprinkle with green onions.

title: margaret's plant food
directions: Mix ingredients together in 1 gallon size jar.
Fill jar with warm water.
Mixture will foam so add slowly.

title: pasta perfects
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Remove to plate and clean grease from pan.
Add butter to pan.
When melted, saute onion, green pepper and garlic until crisp-tender.
Add cream and cook until reduced and thickened.
Add pasta, salt and pepper and toss to mix.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss.
Serve with more cheese on top; crusty bread and Chianti.

title: grandma's baked beans
directions: Place beans in crock-pot; reserve pork fat.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add to crock-pot.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Rinse cauliflower. Break into flowerets.
Cook covered in small amounts of boiling, salted water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain well.

title: chicken & dumplins
directions: With remaining broth drop 1/2 tsp of bisquick mix in boiling broth. Stir occasionally. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add sour cream and coffee. Beat all ingredients about 5 minutes at high speed with electric mixer.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350°, testing doneness at 30 minutes.
Cake should be done at 35 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set to side.
Mix oil, eggs and baby food.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased, floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear relish
directions: Chop this in food chopper.
Put sugar, vinegar, salt and allspice tied in cloth and bring to boil.
Boil 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Brown bacon and drain grease.
Mix all ingredients together in large roaster or casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour, covered, then 20 minutes, uncovered, at 350° to 400°.

title: chili noodle soup
directions: Put tomatoes, water, salt and chili in a kettle and boil. Saute onion and celery in a frypan.
Add beaten eggs and scramble. Then put onion-egg mixture in the chili.
Add seasonings.
Bring to boiling.
Add noodles.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: thai fried broccoli with shrimp
directions: Peel the shrimp.
Cut and clean.
Soak broccoli in cold water for 15 minutes.
Heat the oil in wok over medium heat.
Fry the minced garlic until golden brown.
Add the shrimp, turning over a few times.
Add fish sauce and oyster sauce.
Stir-fry.
Drain the broccoli.
Add to the fried shrimp and stir for 3 minutes.
Spoon onto a serving plate.
Serve with rice.
